Cost: Equals the number of Gnoph Kehs in your Unit pool (i.e. if only one Gnoph Keh is in your pool, the Cost is 1).Spellbook: Berserkergang","product":"Windwalker","tot":"4","img":"/factions/windwalker/unit-mini-gnop-keh.png","url":"/factions/windwalker?units#_gnop-keh","keywords":["unit"]},{"name":"Rhan Tegoth","type":"Great Old One","cost":"6","combat":"3","notes":"How to Awaken Rhan Tegoth:1) Pay 6 Power.2) Rhan Tegoth appears in an Area containing the Windwalker Glyph.Eternal (Post-Battle): If Rhan Tegoth receives a Pain or a Kill, you may pay 1 Power to cancel its effect on him. He can only receive one combat result per Battle.","text":"Cost: 6 Combat: 3
How to Awaken Rhan Tegoth:1) Pay 6 Power.2) Rhan Tegoth appears in an Area containing the Windwalker Glyph.Eternal (Post-Battle): If Rhan Tegoth receives a Pain or a Kill, you may pay 1 Power to cancel its effect on him. He can only receive one combat result per Battle.","product":"Windwalker","tot":"1","img":"/factions/windwalker/unit-mini-rhan-tegoth.png","url":"/factions/windwalker?units#_rhan-tegoth","keywords":["unit"]},{"name":"Ithaqua","type":"Great Old One","cost":"6","combat":"?","notes":"How to Awaken Ithaqua:1) Rhan Tegoth has been awakened (he need not be in play).2) A Gate must exist in an Area marked with your Glyph. You need not control the Gate.3) Pay 6 Power and replace the Gate with Ithaqua.Combat: Equal to half of your opponent's Doom, rounded up.Ferox (Ongoing): While Ithaqua is in play, your Cultists cannot be captured by enemy Monsters or Terrors. They are still vulnerable to enemy Great Old Ones.","text":"Cost: 6 Combat: ?
How to Awaken Ithaqua:1) Rhan Tegoth has been awakened (he need not be in play).2) A Gate must exist in an Area marked with your Glyph. You need not control the Gate.3) Pay 6 Power and replace the Gate with Ithaqua.Combat: Equal to half of your opponent's Doom, rounded up.Ferox (Ongoing): While Ithaqua is in play, your Cultists cannot be captured by enemy Monsters or Terrors. They are still vulnerable to enemy Great Old Ones.","product":"Windwalker","tot":"1","img":"/factions/windwalker/unit-mini-ithaqua.png","url":"/factions/windwalker?units#_ithaqua","keywords":["unit"]},{"name":"Arctic Wind (Ongoing)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Ongoing","text":"When Ithaqua uses Move Action, any or all your Units in the same Area can Move with him for no additional cost.","product":"Windwalker","img":"/factions/windwalker/icon.png","url":"/factions/windwalker?spellbooks","keywords":["faction-spellbook","spellbook"]},{"name":"Berserkergang (Post-Battle)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Post-Battle","text":"For each Gnoph Keh assigned a Kill in Battle, the enemy must Eliminate 1 Monster or Cultist.","product":"Windwalker","img":"/factions/windwalker/icon.png","url":"/factions/windwalker?spellbooks","keywords":["faction-spellbook","spellbook"]},{"name":"Cannibalism (Post-Battle)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Post-Battle","text":"After all Battle results have been applied, if one or more enemy Units were killed, you may place a Wendigo or Acolyte from your Pool into the Battle Area. You may do this even if you were not involved in the Battle.","product":"Windwalker","img":"/factions/windwalker/icon.png","url":"/factions/windwalker?spellbooks","keywords":["faction-spellbook","spellbook"]},{"name":"Herald of the Outer Gods (Ongoing)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Ongoing","text":"Pay 5 Power for Windwalker's Ritual of Annihilation, regardless of the number indicated on the Ritual track.","product":"Windwalker","img":"/factions/windwalker/icon.png","url":"/factions/windwalker?spellbooks","keywords":["faction-spellbook","spellbook"]},{"name":"Howl (Pre-Battle)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Pre-Battle","text":"Before Battle, if any Wendigos are present, you may force the enemy to Retreat one Unit (of their choice) out of the Area to an adjacent Area. This is not a Pain - the Unit may be moved to an Area containing your Units.","product":"Windwalker","img":"/factions/windwalker/icon.png","url":"/factions/windwalker?spellbooks","keywords":["faction-spellbook","spellbook"]},{"name":"Ice Age (Action: Cost 1)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Action: Cost 1","text":"Place or move your Ice Age token to any Area. When an enemy Faction takes any Action ending in the Ice Age Area, they must pay +1 Power.","product":"Windwalker","img":"/factions/windwalker/icon.png","url":"/factions/windwalker?spellbooks","keywords":["faction-spellbook","spellbook"]},{"name":"Rulebook Extras","type":"Neutral Expansion","product":"Neutral Expansions","units":["Asenath Waite","Crawford Tillinghast","Ermengarde Stubbs","Herbert West","Joseph Curwen","Keziah Mason","Lavinia Whateley","Pitpipo","The Eidolon","The Prophetess","Worms of Ghroth","Eradicators","Cthulhu","Hastur","Ithaqua","Nyarlathotep","Rhan-Tegoth","Shub-Niggurath","The King in Yellow","Tsathoggua","Ubbo-Sathla","Yog-Sothoth"],"img":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras/icon.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras","keywords":["product","expansion"]},{"name":"Asenath Waite","type":"Cultist","cost":"3","combat":"0","notes":"The Thing from Beyond (Ongoing): After any player’s Action, choose any enemy Monster or Cultist on the Map and replace it with one of your own Units costing 3 or less (except Asenath Waite), then Eliminate Asenath Waite.","text":"Cost: 3 Combat: 0
The Thing from Beyond (Ongoing): After any player’s Action, choose any enemy Monster or Cultist on the Map and replace it with one of your own Units costing 3 or less (except Asenath Waite), then Eliminate Asenath Waite.","product":"Rulebook Extras","tot":"1","img":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras/unit-mini-asenath-waite.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras?units?asenath-waite","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Crawford Tillinghast","type":"Cultist","cost":"3","combat":"0","notes":"The Ultra-Violet (Pre-Battle): Before any Battle (even if Crawford Tillinghast is not involved), you may Eliminate Crawford Tillinghast and place Monsters and/or Cultists with a total Power cost of up to 3 from your Pool into the Battle Area, off to one side. These Units participate in the Battle, and can use any Pre-Battle or Post-Battle abilities they may have. After the entire Battle is resolved, Eliminate any surviving “extra” Units.","text":"Cost: 3 Combat: 0
