The Pit of Despair (Post-Battle): When you take a Kill in Battle, you can assign it to Pitpipo even if he was not involved in the Battle.","product":"Rulebook Extras","tot":"1","img":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras/unit-mini-pitpipo.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras?units?pitpipo","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"The Eidolon","type":"Cultist","cost":"2; however, once the Eidolon's Loyalty Card is in play, any player can Recruit him.","combat":"0","notes":"Hierarchy (Ongoing):The Eidolon generates 1 Power during the Gather Power Phase. He can be Captured like any Cultist and is Recruited, rather than Summoned. He cannot Create or Control Gates.Eldritch Wisdom (Ongoing):If the Eidolon is in play, after any player's Action you can force each player to write down his or her next Action and then flip this Loyalty Card face-down. Example: an enemy who plans to Move must write \"Move\" but he need not say which Units are Moving, nor to where. On each player's next Action, they must perform that Action unless it is now impossible to do so. In this case, another Action may be taken. Flip this Loyalty Card face-up in the next Doom Phase.","text":"Cost: 2; however, once the Eidolon's Loyalty Card is in play, any player can Recruit him. Combat: 0
Hierarchy (Ongoing):The Eidolon generates 1 Power during the Gather Power Phase. He can be Captured like any Cultist and is Recruited, rather than Summoned. He cannot Create or Control Gates.Eldritch Wisdom (Ongoing):If the Eidolon is in play, after any player's Action you can force each player to write down his or her next Action and then flip this Loyalty Card face-down. Example: an enemy who plans to Move must write \"Move\" but he need not say which Units are Moving, nor to where. On each player's next Action, they must perform that Action unless it is now impossible to do so. In this case, another Action may be taken. Flip this Loyalty Card face-up in the next Doom Phase.","product":"Rulebook Extras","tot":"1","img":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras/unit-mini-the-eidolon.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras?units?the-eidolon","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"The Prophetess","type":"Cultist","cost":"2; however, once the Prophetess' Loyalty Card is in play, any player can recruit her (she still belongs to the Faction which has this Loyalty Card).","combat":"0","notes":"Hierarchy (Ongoing):The Prophetess generates 1 Power during the Gather Power Phase. She can be Captured like any Cultist and is Recruited rather than Summoned. She cannot Create or Control Gates.True Vision (Doom Phase):The player with the highest-ranked Unit in the Area with the Prophetess can pay extra Power when performing a Ritual of Annihilation. That player gains 1 additional Elder Sign for every 3 (additional) Power Spent. Unit rank in order from lowest to highest is Cultist, Monster, Terror, Independent Great Old One, Faction Great Old One. In case of a tie, no one benefits from True Vision.","text":"Cost: 2; however, once the Prophetess' Loyalty Card is in play, any player can recruit her (she still belongs to the Faction which has this Loyalty Card). Combat: 0
Hierarchy (Ongoing):The Prophetess generates 1 Power during the Gather Power Phase. She can be Captured like any Cultist and is Recruited rather than Summoned. She cannot Create or Control Gates.True Vision (Doom Phase):The player with the highest-ranked Unit in the Area with the Prophetess can pay extra Power when performing a Ritual of Annihilation. That player gains 1 additional Elder Sign for every 3 (additional) Power Spent. Unit rank in order from lowest to highest is Cultist, Monster, Terror, Independent Great Old One, Faction Great Old One. In case of a tie, no one benefits from True Vision.","product":"Rulebook Extras","tot":"1","img":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras/unit-mini-the-prophetess.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras?units?the-prophetess","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Worms of Ghroth","type":"Terror","cost":"N/A. Whenever a Worm of Ghroth is Killed or Eliminated, roll a die. If the result is higher than the number of Worms in play, you may place up to two Worms into any available, unoccupied areas of the Map. In the event that multiple Worms are Killed or Eliminated, roll a die for each Worm so removed from play. Resolve this ability one roll at a time.","combat":"0","notes":"Eradication (Gather Power Phase):Roll a die. If the result is equal to or less than the number of Worms of Ghroth in play, gain 1 Elder Sign and lose Power equal to the number shown on the die.Note: The Worms of Ghroth miniatures are found only in the Shaggai Map expansion. Worms of Ghroth cannot be used as Terrors if you are playing on the Shaggai Map.","text":"Cost: N/A. Whenever a Worm of Ghroth is Killed or Eliminated, roll a die. If the result is higher than the number of Worms in play, you may place up to two Worms into any available, unoccupied areas of the Map. In the event that multiple Worms are Killed or Eliminated, roll a die for each Worm so removed from play. Resolve this ability one roll at a time. Combat: 0
Eradication (Gather Power Phase):Roll a die. If the result is equal to or less than the number of Worms of Ghroth in play, gain 1 Elder Sign and lose Power equal to the number shown on the die.Note: The Worms of Ghroth miniatures are found only in the Shaggai Map expansion. Worms of Ghroth cannot be used as Terrors if you are playing on the Shaggai Map.","product":"Rulebook Extras","tot":"6","img":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras/unit-mini-worms-of-ghroth.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras?units?worms-of-ghroth","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Eradicators","type":"Eradicator","cost":"n/a","combat":"n/a","notes":"Anti-Existence (Ongoing): Eradicators are not Units. They cannot Move, nor do they participate in Battle. They cannot be Eliminated or affected by abilities or Spellbooks. Once placed, they are permanent.Overclock (Gather Power Phase): Each player gains 1 Power for each Gate he Controls that shares an Area with an Eradicator, but must choose and Eliminate 1 of his own Units from each of those Areas. The Eradicators' controller instead gains 2 Power for each of his Gates that shares an Area with an Eradicator, but must still Eliminate one of his own Units in each such Area.Annihilate (Doom Phase): Starting with the First Player, each player in turn places 1 Eradicator on the Map into  any Area that does not already have an Eradicator. Once all 15 Eradicators are in play, ignore this ability.","text":"Cost: n/a Combat: n/a
Anti-Existence (Ongoing): Eradicators are not Units. They cannot Move, nor do they participate in Battle. They cannot be Eliminated or affected by abilities or Spellbooks. Once placed, they are permanent.Overclock (Gather Power Phase): Each player gains 1 Power for each Gate he Controls that shares an Area with an Eradicator, but must choose and Eliminate 1 of his own Units from each of those Areas. The Eradicators' controller instead gains 2 Power for each of his Gates that shares an Area with an Eradicator, but must still Eliminate one of his own Units in each such Area.Annihilate (Doom Phase): Starting with the First Player, each player in turn places 1 Eradicator on the Map into  any Area that does not already have an Eradicator. Once all 15 Eradicators are in play, ignore this ability.","product":"Rulebook Extras","tot":15,"img":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras/unit-mini-eradicators.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras?units?eradicators","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Cthulhu","type":"Independent Great Old One","cost":"6","combat":"3","notes":"The Stars are Right (Doom Phase): Gain 1 Elder Sign in each Doom Phase in which you Control a Gate in the Area with Cthulhu’s Glyph.","text":"Cost: 6 Combat: 3
The Stars are Right (Doom Phase): Gain 1 Elder Sign in each Doom Phase in which you Control a Gate in the Area with Cthulhu’s Glyph.","product":"Rulebook Extras","tot":1,"img":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras/unit-mini-cthulhu.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras?units?cthulhu","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Devour (Pre-Battle)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Pre-Battle","text":"Your enemy chooses and eliminates one of his own Monsters or Cultists from the Battle Area.","product":"Rulebook Extras (Cthulhu)","img":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras/unit-sil-cthulhu.svg","url":"/neutral-expansions/rulebook-extras?units?cthulhu","keywords":["spellbook","independent-spellbook"]},{"name":"Hastur","type":"Independent Great Old One","cost":"6","combat":"Equal to half of the current cost of a Ritual of Annihilation (round down).","notes":"The Stars are Wrong (Doom Phase): Gain 1 Elder Sign during each Doom Phase in which you Control a Gate in the Area containing Yellow Sign’s Faction Glyph (NOT one of the King in Yellow’s  3 Spellbook Glyphs, but the Yellow Sign, itself).","text":"Cost: 6 Combat: Equal to half of the current cost of a Ritual of Annihilation (round down).
