Loathsome Titter (Gather Power Phase):Brown Jenkin shares an area with an enemy-controlled Gate during the Gather Power Phase, gain 2 Power, plus 1 more power for each enemy Cultist in the area..Familiar (Ongoing):If Brown Jenkin is killed or eliminated, if (or as soon as) you have at least 2 Power, pay 2 Power and place Brown Jenkin at your Controlled Gate. This does not count as an Action. This is not Optional.","product":"Kickstarter Specials","tot":"1","img":"/neutral-expansions/kickstarter-specials/unit-mini-brown-jenkin.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/kickstarter-specials?units?brown-jenkin","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Elder Shoggoth","type":"Terror","cost":"4","combat":"2","notes":"Prime Cause (Post-Battle):In a Battle involving the Elder Shoggoth, choose any of you Units (including this one) and replace it with any other Unit from your Pool. You can gain a Faction Great Old One that was previously Awakened, but still must fulfill other requirements (for example, to place Cthulhu, the Battle must be in his Start Area, plus a gate). If you choose to replace the Elder Shoggoth itself, pay nothing, and no enemy gains a reward. Otherwise, follow these rules:Pay half the new Unit's Power cost (rounded down–so you pay 1 Power for a cost 3 Monster).If the new Unit is a Terror, the enemy gains 1 Doom.If the new Unit is a Great Old One, the enemy gains 1 Elder Sign.","text":"Cost: 4 Combat: 2
Prime Cause (Post-Battle):In a Battle involving the Elder Shoggoth, choose any of you Units (including this one) and replace it with any other Unit from your Pool. You can gain a Faction Great Old One that was previously Awakened, but still must fulfill other requirements (for example, to place Cthulhu, the Battle must be in his Start Area, plus a gate). If you choose to replace the Elder Shoggoth itself, pay nothing, and no enemy gains a reward. Otherwise, follow these rules:Pay half the new Unit's Power cost (rounded down–so you pay 1 Power for a cost 3 Monster).If the new Unit is a Terror, the enemy gains 1 Doom.If the new Unit is a Great Old One, the enemy gains 1 Elder Sign.","product":"Kickstarter Specials","tot":"1","img":"/neutral-expansions/kickstarter-specials/unit-mini-elder-shoggoth.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/kickstarter-specials?units?elder-shoggoth","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Cthulhu, the Harbinger","type":"Independent Great Old One","cost":"8","combat":"n/a","notes":"Great Old One (Ongoing): Harbinger Cthulhu cannot be Moved from its Area by any means except by destroying it, and has no Spellbook. When Battled, all the attacker's Units in the Area are destroyed in the Battle. It takes at least 3 Kills and/or Eliminates in the same Combat to Kill Harbinger Cthulhu.When Harbinger Cthulhu is Killed, return all the Units from this Loyalty Card to Harbinger's Cthulhu Area. The player who Killed Harbinger Cthulhu gets 1 Elder Sign, as does the Controller of Harbinger Cthulhu, even if they are the same person.","text":"Cost: 8 Combat: n/a
Great Old One (Ongoing): Harbinger Cthulhu cannot be Moved from its Area by any means except by destroying it, and has no Spellbook. When Battled, all the attacker's Units in the Area are destroyed in the Battle. It takes at least 3 Kills and/or Eliminates in the same Combat to Kill Harbinger Cthulhu.When Harbinger Cthulhu is Killed, return all the Units from this Loyalty Card to Harbinger's Cthulhu Area. The player who Killed Harbinger Cthulhu gets 1 Elder Sign, as does the Controller of Harbinger Cthulhu, even if they are the same person.","product":"Kickstarter Specials","tot":1,"img":"/neutral-expansions/kickstarter-specials/unit-mini-cthulhu-the-harbinger.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/kickstarter-specials?units?cthulhu-the-harbinger","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Dire Azathoth","type":"Independent Great Old One","cost":"10","combat":"Roll a die. Dire Azathoth's Combat rating is equal to the result of the roll.","notes":"Mindless Destruction (Post-Battle): Any Faction Battling in Dire Azathoth's Area gains his choice of either 1 Doom or 1 Power for every Unit that Faction Kills or Eliminates in that Battle. (Dire Azathoth need not be involved in the Battle).","text":"Cost: 10 Combat: Roll a die. Dire Azathoth's Combat rating is equal to the result of the roll.
