Too Short (Pre-Battle): If Procrustes is in the Battle, select an enemy Unit and roll 1d6. If the roll is lower than the enemy Unit's Cost, immediately Eliminate that Unit. If the roll is Higher than the enemy Unit's Cost, Eliminate one of your own Units instead (your choice). This ability is not optional.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover","tot":1,"img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-mini-procrustes.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?procrustes","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Too Tall (Ongoing)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Ongoing","text":"You must apply the Too Short ability to all Battles in which you participate, not just those including Procrustes.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover (Procrustes)","img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-sil-procrustes.svg","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?procrustes","keywords":["spellbook","independent-spellbook"]},{"name":"Pulgasaur","type":"Independent Great Old One","cost":"6","combat":"4","notes":"Metamorphosis (Post-Battle): The first time the Pulgasaur receives a Kill, instead he gains his Spellbook. The second time he receives a Kill, instead flip his Spellbook face-down.","text":"Cost: 6 Combat: 4
Metamorphosis (Post-Battle): The first time the Pulgasaur receives a Kill, instead he gains his Spellbook. The second time he receives a Kill, instead flip his Spellbook face-down.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover","tot":1,"img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-mini-pulgasaur.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?pulgasaur","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Final Metamorphosis (Post-Battle)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Post-Battle","text":"If this Spellbook is face-down when the Pulgasaur receives a Kill, it is, at last, Killed.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover (Pulgasaur)","img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-sil-pulgasaur.svg","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?pulgasaur","keywords":["spellbook","independent-spellbook"]},{"name":"Scylla","type":"Independent Great Old One","cost":"4","combat":"1 per remaining head","notes":"Multicapitus (Post-Battle):  When a Kill or Elimination is scored against Scylla, instead discard one of her Head markers. She dies when her last Head marker is discarded. Multiple Kills or Eliminations can be targeted vs. her.","text":"Cost: 4 Combat: 1 per remaining head
Multicapitus (Post-Battle):  When a Kill or Elimination is scored against Scylla, instead discard one of her Head markers. She dies when her last Head marker is discarded. Multiple Kills or Eliminations can be targeted vs. her.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover","tot":1,"img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-mini-scylla.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?scylla","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Regeneration (Once-Only)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Once-Only","text":"All Scylla's lost heads are restored, but you do not gain any extra Doom for this Ritual (you still earn Elder Signs). This Spellbook is not optional.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover (Scylla)","img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-sil-scylla.svg","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?scylla","keywords":["spellbook","independent-spellbook"]},{"name":"Stheno","type":"Independent Great Old One","cost":"4","combat":"0","notes":"Fossilization (Action: Cost 1):  Select an enemy Unit in Stheno's Area or an adjacent Area. It is laid on its side, and is considered \"Fossilized\". To Move that Unit, the owner must pay 1 extra Power. It can still be Pained or Moved involuntary by some other Action (such as Black Goat's Avatar).","text":"Cost: 4 Combat: 0
Fossilization (Action: Cost 1):  Select an enemy Unit in Stheno's Area or an adjacent Area. It is laid on its side, and is considered \"Fossilized\". To Move that Unit, the owner must pay 1 extra Power. It can still be Pained or Moved involuntary by some other Action (such as Black Goat's Avatar).","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover","tot":1,"img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-mini-stheno.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?stheno","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Solidification (Ongoing)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Ongoing","text":"When a new Unit is Fossilized, you must select an already Fossilized Unit and stand it up again, if any are available.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover (Stheno)","img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-sil-stheno.svg","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?stheno","keywords":["spellbook","independent-spellbook"]},{"name":"Stroma","type":"Independent Great Old One","cost":"2","combat":"0","notes":"Maelstrom (Ongoing): Stroma cannot Move, nor be Moved, by any means, and neither can any other Unit in her area, regardless of ownership. This includes Pains inflicted in Battle.","text":"Cost: 2 Combat: 0
Maelstrom (Ongoing): Stroma cannot Move, nor be Moved, by any means, and neither can any other Unit in her area, regardless of ownership. This includes Pains inflicted in Battle.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover","tot":1,"img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-mini-stroma.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?stroma","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Whirlpool (Doom Phase)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Doom Phase","text":"Choose one Unit in Stroma's Area and Eliminate it. If no enemy Units are present, you must select your own. If Stroma is alone, Eliminate her.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover (Stroma)","img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-sil-stroma.svg","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?stroma","keywords":["spellbook","independent-spellbook"]},{"name":"Tarasque","type":"Independent Great Old One","cost":"4","combat":"5","notes":"Spined (Post-Battle): If a Kill is scored against the Tarasque, inflict 2 additional Eliminations on the enemy.","text":"Cost: 4 Combat: 5
Spined (Post-Battle): If a Kill is scored against the Tarasque, inflict 2 additional Eliminations on the enemy.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover","tot":1,"img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-mini-tarasque.png","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?tarasque","keywords":["unit","neutral-unit"]},{"name":"Extinguish (Pre-Battle)","type":"Spellbook","cost":"Pre-Battle","text":"In an enemy Great Old One is in the Battle, Tarasque's Combat is 0, and he cannot apply his Spined ability.","product":"Planet Apocalypse Crossover (Tarasque)","img":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover/unit-sil-tarasque.svg","url":"/neutral-expansions/planet-apocalypse-crossover?units?tarasque","keywords":["spellbook","independent-spellbook"]},{"name":"Earth","type":"Map","product":"Maps","img":"/maps/earth/icon.png","url":"/maps/earth","keywords":["product","map"]},{"name":"Dreamlands","type":"Map","product":"Maps","img":"/maps/dreamlands/icon.png","url":"/maps/dreamlands","keywords":["product","map"]},{"name":"Library at Celaeno","type":"Map","product":"Maps","img":"/maps/library-at-celaeno/icon.png","url":"/maps/library-at-celaeno","keywords":["product","map"]},{"name":"Primeval Earth","type":"Map","product":"Maps","img":"/maps/primeval-earth/icon.png","url":"/maps/primeval-earth","keywords":["product","map"]},{"name":"Shaggai","type":"Map","product":"Maps","img":"/maps/shaggai/icon.png","url":"/maps/shaggai","keywords":["product","map"]},{"name":"Yuggoth","type":"Map","product":"Maps","img":"/maps/yuggoth/icon.png","url":"/maps/yuggoth","keywords":["product","map"]},{"name":"Q.  How much Power does Crawling Chaos get for Killing or Paining Cthulhu?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. He receives 2 Power, since that is now half the cost of Awakening Cthulhu (since, obviously, he has already been Awakened once). Of course, he could instead just take 2 Elder Signs. That’s what I would do, anyway.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qHowMuchPowerDoesCrawlingChaosGetForKillingOrPainingCthulhu","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Yellow Sign’s Undead and Byakhee have Combat ratings that change depending on how many are present in the Area. If an Undead or Byakhee is exempted via Invisibility, does it affect the Combat of the remaining Units?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. An Invisible Unit does not count as being “present” in the Area for any purpose. If you have two Undead in an Area and one is turned Invisible, the remaining Undead rolls 0 dice, not 1. The intent is that Invisibility is supposed to be useful.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qYellowSignsUndeadAndByakheeHaveCombatRatingsThatChangeDependingOnHowManyArePresentInTheAreaIfAnUndeadOrByakheeIsExemptedViaInvisibilityDoesItAffectTheCombatOfTheRemainingUnits","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When Yellow Sign takes the Screaming Dead or He Who is Not to be Named Action, does he have to pay the normal Power cost for his second, subsequent Action?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. Yes! For instance, if he Moved using Screaming Dead and then immediately attempted a Desecration, this would cost him a total of 3 Power (or 2 Power, if Third Eye was in effect).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qWhenYellowSignTakesTheScreamingDeadOrHeWhoIsNotToBeNamedActionDoesHeHaveToPayTheNormalPowerCostForHisSecondSubsequentAction","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When Crawling Chaos’s Thousand Forms or Black Goat’s Ghroth abilities are used, can a player insist on taking part of the loss, even if the other players don’t want him to? What if a player has no Power or no Cultists—can he “disagree” with the division?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. In the first case, this would count as a disagreement which needs to be resolved. In the second, if a player refuses to or cannot contribute to the effect, he does not participate in further negotiations and his agreement is immaterial.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qWhenCrawlingChaossThousandFormsOrBlackGoatsGhrothAbilitiesAreUsedCanAPlayerInsistOnTakingPartOfTheLossEvenIfTheOtherPlayersDontWantHimToWhatIfAPlayerHasNoPowerOrNoCultistsCanHeDisagreeWithTheDivision","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Black Goat is in a Battle and uses Necrophagy, can the Ghoul that was sent to the Battle also be assigned the Pain that it added?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. No, the newly-called Ghoul cannot be chosen to be assigned the extra Pain, because it did not participate in the Battle, it only added a Pain result.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qIfBlackGoatIsInABattleAndUsesNecrophagyCanTheGhoulThatWasSentToTheBattleAlsoBeAssignedThePainThatItAdded","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If a Ghoul is already in the target Area but is not participating in the Battle (due to Invisibility), can it stay there and use Necrophagy?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. Yes! An Invisible Ghoul is “not involved” and thus could react via Necrophagy!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qIfAGhoulIsAlreadyInTheTargetAreaButIsNotParticipatingInTheBattleDueToInvisibilityCanItStayThereAndUseNecrophagy","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I fail a Ghroth roll, is the free Acolyte (of any Faction) an optional placement?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. No. Abilities themselves are always optional (unless stated otherwise on their text), but if you choose to use an Ability, you must then do what it says—once you choose to use Ghroth, you cannot simply decide to avoid the consequences! You knew what you were getting into when you joined with Black Goat’s cult!Basically, a failed Ghroth is still intended to be a good thing; Black Goat usually has Acolytes in its Pool, but if not, this can be used to place an enemy Acolyte into an Area with your Monsters so that you can Capture it! Or, you might help a potential ally, perhaps even requesting that they do something for you on their turn in return for your giving them a free Acolyte.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qIfIFailAGhrothRollIsTheFreeAcolyteOfAnyFactionAnOptionalPlacement","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Similar to the question above, but what if I want to use Ghroth, but there are NO Acolytes remaining to be placed in any Faction’s Pool (in case of a failed roll)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. If you fail, then nothing happens! This is not similar to abilities such as Zingaya, which prevents from using the ability if there are no Undead in your Pool with which to replace the enemy Acolyte. With Ghroth, chance is involved - you could Eliminate enemy Cultists (which is the main purpose of Ghroth). To be clear, because you cannot normally choose to fulfill only part of an ability, Ghroth’s free Acolyte is a compensation you cannot refuse. But, having no Cultists to place does not prevent you from attempting a Ghroth roll.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qSimilarToTheQuestionAboveButWhatIfIWantToUseGhrothButThereAreNoAcolytesRemainingToBePlacedInAnyFactionsPoolInCaseOfAFailedRoll","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can other Factions use Move-like actions, such as Avatar or Submerge, to transfer Units to the Moon?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. Yes. They just can’t use the Move action itself, nor actions that specifically mimic Move (like Screaming Dead).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qCanOtherFactionsUseMoveLikeActionsSuchAsAvatarOrSubmergeToTransferUnitsToTheMoon","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Regarding Crawling Chaos’s Madness Spellbook, must he obey normal restrictions on Retreating Units (i.e., not into an Area containing Units of the Faction just Battled)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. Yes, he must obey normal Retreat rules. He also does not get to choose WHICH Units Retreat, only their destination. Also note that with Madness, Crawling Chaos can Retreat players in either order. That is, he may Retreat the defender first.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qRegardingCrawlingChaossMadnessSpellbookMustHeObeyNormalRestrictionsOnRetreatingUnitsIENotIntoAnAreaContainingUnitsOfTheFactionJustBattled","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Since Nyarlathotep cannot be Eliminated due to being surrounded (when he has Emissary of the Outer Gods and is not Battling an enemy Great Old One), can he still “soak up” that Elimination to protect his other Units?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. Yes!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qSinceNyarlathotepCannotBeEliminatedDueToBeingSurroundedWhenHeHasEmissaryOfTheOuterGodsAndIsNotBattlingAnEnemyGreatOldOneCanHeStillSoakUpThatEliminationToProtectHisOtherUnits","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What happens when Crawling Chaos uses Thousand Forms and the number rolled is higher than the sum of all other players’ power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Core Game Rules","text":"A. Crawling Chaos gets Power equal to the die roll.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/core-game-rules#qWhatHappensWhenCrawlingChaosUsesThousandFormsAndTheNumberRolledIsHigherThanTheSumOfAllOtherPlayersPower","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If there is more than one enemy Great Old One in a Battle against me and I invoke Unholy Ground, can I remove two Cathedrals to Eliminate two Great Old Ones?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfThereIsMoreThanOneEnemyGreatOldOneInABattleAgainstMeAndIInvokeUnholyGroundCanIRemoveTwoCathedralsToEliminateTwoGreatOldOnes","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Rhan Tegoth avoid Unholy Ground’s Kill by spending 1 Power as per his Eternal Ability?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, because Unholy Ground produces an Elimination, not a Kill.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanRhanTegothAvoidUnholyGroundsKillBySpending1PowerAsPerHisEternalAbility","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can I use Unholy Ground to Eliminate Azathoth or the Watcher of the Green Pyramid?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. Unlike other Units, the Watcher just loses 1 from his strength when he is “Eliminated”, and Azathoth loses 1 die from his Combat.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIUseUnholyGroundToEliminateAzathothOrTheWatcherOfTheGreenPyramid","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I remove Cathedrals via Unholy Ground, where can I rebuild them?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. When replacing a removed Cathedral, you must obey Cathedral placement rules. For example, if you removed a Cathedral from a particular Yellow Sign Glyph’s Area, and all your other Cathedrals were in play, you could only rebuild it in an Area with that same Yellow Sign Glyph.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIRemoveCathedralsViaUnholyGroundWhereCanIRebuildThem","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I have Reanimated in an Area by themselves, can I use them to take actions besides Move, Capture, or Battle?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, if such Actions are available to you.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIHaveReanimatedInAnAreaByThemselvesCanIUseThemToTakeActionsBesidesMoveCaptureOrBattle","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Do Reanimated need to be accompanied by another Unit to Move?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. They simply need to start their Move in an Area with another friendly (non-Reanimated) Unit.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoReanimatedNeedToBeAccompaniedByAnotherUnitToMove","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If an enemy Great Old One is assigned a Kill, and that Kill is later turned into a Pain (e.g. Nyarlathotep’s Emis-sary of the Outer Gods Spellbook), can Unholy Ground still be used to Eliminate the Great Old One?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, the intent is that Ancients can Eliminate Nyarlathotep with Unholy Ground.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfAnEnemyGreatOldOneIsAssignedAKillAndThatKillIsLaterTurnedIntoAPainEGNyarlathotepsEmisSaryOfTheOuterGodsSpellbookCanUnholyGroundStillBeUsedToEliminateTheGreatOldOne","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can the Ancients Recruit a Cultist in an Area where they only have a Cathedral?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, a Cathedral is not a Unit.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanTheAncientsRecruitACultistInAnAreaWhereTheyOnlyHaveACathedral","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Opener of the Way use They Break Through when the Ancients allow everyone to Summon their cheap-est / most expensive monster?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanOpenerOfTheWayUseTheyBreakThroughWhenTheAncientsAllowEveryoneToSummonTheirCheapEstMostExpensiveMonster","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How do the Ancients generally interact with requirements or rules necessitating all Factions to have a Great Old One?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. The Ancients are ignored for this purpose. For example, the Ancients need not have a Great Old One for an independent Azathoth’s controller to earn his Nuclear Chaos Spellbook.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoTheAncientsGenerallyInteractWithRequirementsOrRulesNecessitatingAllFactionsToHaveAGreatOldOne","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When Yellow Sign takes the Screaming Dead or He Who is Not to be Named Action, does he have to pay the normal Power cost for his second, subsequent Action?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes! For instance, if he Moved using Screaming Dead and then immediately attempted a Desecration, this would cost him a total of 3 Power (or 2 Power, if Third Eye was in effect).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhenYellowSignTakesTheScreamingDeadOrHeWhoIsNotToBeNamedActionDoesHeHaveToPayTheNormalPowerCostForHisSecondSubsequentAction","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Do I get an Elder Sign for Ritualing with Bastet if I’m not using her Requires Attention ability?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. Elder Gods do not provide Elder Signs for Rituals of Annihilation, except in conjunction with special abilities. Also, since Bubastis can only “Control” one Gate (the Moon), a non-Requires Attention ritual only ever adds 1 Doom. Finally, if you DO use the Requires Attention ritual, you do NOT add another 1 Doom for the Moon’s “Gate.” You only get the flat 4 Doom bonus. Really, it’s Bastet adding 3 Doom, plus the 1 extra for the Moon, so you’re not losing anything.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoIGetAnElderSignForRitualingWithBastetIfImNotUsingHerRequiresAttentionAbility","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. The Zagazig Spellbook seems to apply to both sides in a Battle. Is this so? Does it also reverse Kills & Pains for my opponent?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. If you choose to use Zagazig, both sides get the benefits","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qTheZagazigSpellbookSeemsToApplyToBothSidesInABattleIsThisSoDoesItAlsoReverseKillsPainsForMyOpponent","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What happens in a Battle with Sleeper if Bubastis chooses to both use Zagazig and chooses option 2 from Sleeper’s Demand Sacrifice (“All of their Kill results against your Units in this Battle count as Pains, instead.”)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. First Zagazig changes Bubastis’ rolled Kills to Pains, and rolled Pains to Kills. Then all of Bubastis’ rolled Kill results count as Pains due to Demand Sacrifice. Sleeper’s rolled Kills and Pains are reversed as per Zagazig.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhatHappensInABattleWithSleeperIfBubastisChoosesToBothUseZagazigAndChoosesOption2FromSleepersDemandSacrificeAllOfTheirKillResultsAgainstYourUnitsInThisBattleCountAsPainsInstead","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Since Spellbooks target Earth Cats as they would Cultists, can they be Captured?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. They’re not Cultists, though Dreams, Zingaya, and Ghroth treat them that way. Crawling Chaos can never get his “Capture” Spellbook requirement from Bubastis, which means you can’t use Crawling Chaos and Bubastis as opponents in a 2-player game. Except as a prank, I guess.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qSinceSpellbooksTargetEarthCatsAsTheyWouldCultistsCanTheyBeCaptured","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Bastet is in a Battle by herself, does she still get to inﬂict her one Kill, even though no Combat dice are rolled for her side?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, of course. Elder Gods just inflict results. They don’t roll dice, and they don’t require dice to be rolled for their results to take place. Also, if Bastet is alone, she also still gets her ability to reduce the enemy-rolled Kills by 1.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfBastetIsInABattleByHerselfDoesSheStillGetToInﬂictHerOneKillEvenThoughNoCombatDiceAreRolledForHerSide","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If no Earth Cats are in play, how can I get more of them?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. You’d have to Summon them on the Moon, which always counts as an Area with a Controlled Gate.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfNoEarthCatsAreInPlayHowCanIGetMoreOfThem","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Opener of the Way use They Break Through on the Moon? How about The Beyond One?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, he can use They Break Through. No, he cannot “Move” the Moon via Beyond One. He also cannot Move a Gate TO the Moon, because there is already a Gate present. He can’t Move Yog-Sothoth to the Moon, but he could Awaken him there, if he had a Spawn of Yog-Sothoth on the Moon.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanOpenerOfTheWayUseTheyBreakThroughOnTheMoonHowAboutTheBeyondOne","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What happens if Sleeper uses Ancient Sorcery to target Bubastis?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Nothing, unless he has some way to add Earth Cats to his faction.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhatHappensIfSleeperUsesAncientSorceryToTargetBubastis","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Sleeper uses Burrowing to Move 2 Units from the Moon back to the main Map, how much Power does Bubastis get, if Catnapping is in eﬀect?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. She gets two Power, because Sleeper must first pay 2 Power to Move the two Units. He then gets a refund of 1 Power back, but that doesn’t apply to Bubastis.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfSleeperUsesBurrowingToMove2UnitsFromTheMoonBackToTheMainMapHowMuchPowerDoesBubastisGetIfCatnappingIsInEﬀect","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If a player gets the Dark Demon (from the Masks expansion), how does this aﬀect Bubastis?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. She gets stuck with a Dark Demon, like anyone else and loses an Earth Cat, Because spells affect her Earth Cats as if they were Cultists, this means she cannot Summon Earth Cats unless her Dark Demon is in play.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfAPlayerGetsTheDarkDemonFromTheMasksExpansionHowDoesThisAﬀectBubastis","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. On the Primeval Earth Map, does a Glacier appear on the Moon during the ﬁrst Doom phase?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, because Control may not be seized from Bubastis, including by a Glacier. I guess you could put a Glacier there if you wanted, but it would have no effect.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qOnThePrimevalEarthMapDoesAGlacierAppearOnTheMoonDuringTheFIrstDoomPhase","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. On the Yuggoth Map, can Earth Cats be turned into Brain Cylinders?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qOnTheYuggothMapCanEarthCatsBeTurnedIntoBrainCylinders","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Several Independent Units aﬀect Cultists. When under your control, do these work on Earth Cats? (e.g. Eihort)","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qSeveralIndependentUnitsAﬀectCultistsWhenUnderYourControlDoTheseWorkOnEarthCatsEGEihort","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Is the Moon tile considered adjacent to all tiles for Spellbooks and Abilities?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIsTheMoonTileConsideredAdjacentToAllTilesForSpellbooksAndAbilities","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Bastet is in an area with Yog-Sothoth, and you ritual, do you get 3 Elder Signs?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. But the presence of another Enemy Controlled Gate does not increase this reward.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfBastetIsInAnAreaWithYogSothothAndYouRitualDoYouGet3ElderSigns","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Can Earth Cats be given up to Blood Offering in exchange for Elder Signs?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. Although they aren’t technically “being Captured,” the Action still results in them being Captured, so the answer is no.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanEarthCatsBeGivenUpToBloodOfferingInExchangeForElderSigns","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If I leave the Moon while at 0 Power (using Eternal Servitude), does Bubastis get Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. Actual Power was not spent.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfILeaveTheMoonWhileAt0PowerUsingEternalServitudeDoesBubastisGetPower","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How can I change the position of the Azathoth marker on the Doom Track?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. The Daemon Sultan Faction can change the marker’s position each time you Awaken Avatar Thesis.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowCanIChangeThePositionOfTheAzathothMarkerOnTheDoomTrack","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When the independent neutral Great Old One Azathoth (from the Azathoth expansion) is Awakened, he rolls the Azathoth die, and places the marker on the track. Does this still happen if Daemon Sultan is in the game?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, of course. For example, say Daemon Sultan Awakened Avatar Thesis, paying 2 Power. The Azathoth Glyph Token is set to 2. Then, on the next turn, a player Awakens the independent Azathoth. As part of that process, he rolls the Azathoth die and scores 7. The Azathoth Glyph Token is therefore moved from 2 to 7. Now, if Daemon Sultan Awakens Azathoth Antithesis, he’ll only have to pay 1 Power.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhenTheIndependentNeutralGreatOldOneAzathothFromTheAzathothExpansionIsAwakenedHeRollsTheAzathothDieAndPlacesTheMarkerOnTheTrackDoesThisStillHappenIfDaemonSultanIsInTheGame","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. In the rare case that another Faction’s Start Area is the ﬁrst Area in which Daemon Sultan places a Cultist, where is Daemon Sultan’s Start Area?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. In that rare case, that start area counts as both Daemon Sultan and the other Faction’s start. Place his token there.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qInTheRareCaseThatAnotherFactionsStartAreaIsTheFIrstAreaInWhichDaemonSultanPlacesACultistWhereIsDaemonSultansStartArea","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. The neutral Azathoth Spellbook Umr-at-Tawil makes Gates cost 1 less. Does this have an eﬀect on the Chaos Gate Spellbook?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. Using the Chaos Gate Spellbook still costs 1 Power.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qTheNeutralAzathothSpellbookUmrAtTawilMakesGatesCost1LessDoesThisHaveAnEﬀectOnTheChaosGateSpellbook","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I’m in a Battle and I assign Kills to both Avatar Thesis and Avatar Antithesis, can I then use Synthesis’s Cosmic Ruler ability to “transfer” Avatar Thesis’s death to Avatar Antithesis, thus saving the latter?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. You can only use Cosmic Ruler to transfer a death to an Avatar which isn’t already being Killed in the Battle. In other words, you can’t use it to “double up” Kills in this way.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfImInABattleAndIAssignKillsToBothAvatarThesisAndAvatarAntithesisCanIThenUseSynthesissCosmicRulerAbilityToTransferAvatarThesissDeathToAvatarAntithesisThusSavingTheLatter","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Daemon Sultan use Psychosis to place a Cultist in an area with an Abandoned Gate? How about a Chaos Gate or a Cathedral?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, if no Unit is present. Gates, Chaos Gates, and Cathedrals are buildings, not Units.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanDaemonSultanUsePsychosisToPlaceACultistInAnAreaWithAnAbandonedGateHowAboutAChaosGateOrACathedral","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. On the Primeval Map, does a Glacier appear in Daemon Sultan’s Start Area in the ﬁrst Doom Phase?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, even if no Gate is present.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qOnThePrimevalMapDoesAGlacierAppearInDaemonSultansStartAreaInTheFIrstDoomPhase","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can abilities which aﬀect Gates, such as Beyond One, or Ithaqua’s Awakening, target a Chaos Gate?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanAbilitiesWhichAﬀectGatesSuchAsBeyondOneOrIthaquasAwakeningTargetAChaosGate","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When using the Traitors spellbook, who chooses the Cultist to be placed on the Gate? Can your enemy place their High Priest?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. The Daemon Sultan player chooses and they can select any Cultist. This includes High Priests, Eihort Brood Tokens, Brain Cylinders, etc., assuming that Eihort or Brain Cylinders are in this game.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhenUsingTheTraitorsSpellbookWhoChoosesTheCultistToBePlacedOnTheGateCanYourEnemyPlaceTheirHighPriest","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Can Animate Matter move into a Lord’s Shadow Area?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Yes. If there is a normal Gate there, it is destroyed. Otherwise, the Daemon Sultan now likely just acquired a nice reward\nby subverting Control of that Lord’s Shadow for minimal investment. Watch out for Animate Matter! Try and keep a Gryllus\naround to Scavenge potential Animate Matter situations.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanAnimateMatterMoveIntoALordsShadowArea","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Key and the Gate Work?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Opener gets 2 Power for Yog-Sothoth during the Gather Power Phase. He also gets 1 Doom for having Yog-Sothoth on the Map during the Doom Phase. If he performs a Ritual of Annihilation, he gets 1 point for Yog-Sothoth as a Gate (plus an Elder Sign for Yog-Sothoth as a Great Old One).
As a Gate, Yog-Sothoth can always Summon Monsters into his Area. Unlike other Gates, he can coexist with a normal Gate, and he is never considered to be Abandoned. Cultists do not Control him, nor can they ride him. He cannot be Moved with The Beyond One as if he were a Gate.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoesKeyAndTheGateWork","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does Yog-Sothoth provide Power to Cthulhu via Y’ha Nthlei if he is in an ocean?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, because Yog-Sothoth is an Enemy-controlled Gate in the ocean!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoesYogSothothProvidePowerToCthulhuViaYhaNthleiIfHeIsInAnOcean","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Yog-Sothoth is in the Area where Ithaqua is Awakened, do you have to replace Yog-Sothoth (as the Gate) with Ithaqua?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. If Yog-Sothoth is the ONLY Gate in the Area, then yes. If there is another available Gate, then you must replace THAT Gate with Ithaqua instead.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfYogSothothIsInTheAreaWhereIthaquaIsAwakenedDoYouHaveToReplaceYogSothothAsTheGateWithIthaqua","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can I use Beyond One to teleport a Gate to an Area containing Yog-Sothoth, since he is also a Gate?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Despite this fact, yes, you can Beyond One to Yog-Sothoth’s Area.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIUseBeyondOneToTeleportAGateToAnAreaContainingYogSothothSinceHeIsAlsoAGate","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Do enemy Great Old Ones still cancel Beyond One if the Gate in question is not Controlled by their Faction?And do enemy Independent Great Old Ones still cancel it, too? What about the Watcher from the Yuggoth expansion?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, to all three.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoEnemyGreatOldOnesStillCancelBeyondOneIfTheGateInQuestionIsNotControlledByTheirFactionAndDoEnemyIndependentGreatOldOnesStillCancelItTooWhatAboutTheWatcherFromTheYuggothExpansion","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If an Opener of the Way Unit in an Area is turned Invisible by a Flying Polyp, does it count as “participating in a Battle” for the purpose of getting promoted by Million Favored Ones?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. The Invisibility Spellbook states that the Unit “takes no part in the rest of the Battle.” This includes all Post-Battle abilities and effects.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfAnOpenerOfTheWayUnitInAnAreaIsTurnedInvisibleByAFlyingPolypDoesItCountAsParticipatingInABattleForThePurposeOfGettingPromotedByMillionFavoredOnes","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I have a Mutant and an Abomination eligible to promote via Million Favored Ones, but I do not have an Abomination figure in my Pool, can I first promote the Abomination, then the Mutant (now that an Abomination figure has returned to the Pool)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. You can cycle Units through your Pool in this way to promote them.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIHaveAMutantAndAnAbominationEligibleToPromoteViaMillionFavoredOnesButIDoNotHaveAnAbominationFigureInMyPoolCanIFirstPromoteTheAbominationThenTheMutantNowThatAnAbominationFigureHasReturnedToThePool","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I promote a Spawn of Yog-Sothoth into 2 or more Mutants via Million Favored Ones, and that Spawn was Pained in the Battle, are all of his Mutant “progeny” Pained?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Million Favored Ones happens after all the Pains and Kills are applied, so the Spawn first Retreats into a neighboring Area and THEN shatters into multiple Mutants. This also means that if a Spawn is Eliminated by a Pain result because it was surrounded by its opponent, you do not receive the Mutants.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIPromoteASpawnOfYogSothothInto2OrMoreMutantsViaMillionFavoredOnesAndThatSpawnWasPainedInTheBattleAreAllOfHisMutantProgenyPained","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Windwalker’s Howl is used to Retreat one of Opener’s Monsters, can it still promote via Million Favored Ones?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, they do not participate in the rest of the Battle and so cannot use their abilities.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfWindwalkersHowlIsUsedToRetreatOneOfOpenersMonstersCanItStillPromoteViaMillionFavoredOnes","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How do Battle abilities interact with Dread Curse of Azathoth?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Dread Curse is not considered a Battle, despite the fact that Combat dice are rolled. It cannot be combined with Channel Power or any other Pre-Battle, Battle, or Post-Battle effects (such as Regeneration, Necrophagy, or even Madness).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoBattleAbilitiesInteractWithDreadCurseOfAzathoth","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Who selects the targets of Dread Curse of Azathoth?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. The victim selects the targets; you just choose which results apply to which Faction. Thus, if you rolled a Kill and two Pains, you could apply the Kill and a Pain to one Faction, and the remaining Pain to another.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhoSelectsTheTargetsOfDreadCurseOfAzathoth","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Regarding Dread Curse of Azathoth, to where do Pained Units Retreat?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. After the victim selects which Units are Pained, Opener of the Way selects to which adjacent Area each Unit Retreats. He can include Areas that contain Opener of the Way Units (these Units cannot be Eliminated by being surrounded).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qRegardingDreadCurseOfAzathothToWhereDoPainedUnitsRetreat","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can the Dread Curse of Azathoth be used to attack Units that are not Controlled by any Faction, such the Dreamlands Surface Map’s Zoogs, or Abhoth’s Filth tokens after Abhoth has been Killed?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, because that Spellbook requires you to apply the Combat results to particular Factions. In the case of Abhoth, once he is back in play the Filth tokens may be targeted, but as the Zoogs are never under the Control of a particular Faction they can never be targeted.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanTheDreadCurseOfAzathothBeUsedToAttackUnitsThatAreNotControlledByAnyFactionSuchTheDreamlandsSurfaceMapsZoogsOrAbhothsFilthTokensAfterAbhothHasBeenKilled","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can I use Channel Power more than once in the same Battle?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. You can keep re-rolling misses (rolls of one, two or three), paying one Power per re-roll, until you run out of Power or all the dice score results.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIUseChannelPowerMoreThanOnceInTheSameBattle","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can I use Dragon Ascending even if I am out of Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, because it is not an Action—it is simply an effect that you can apply at any time.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIUseDragonAscendingEvenIfIAmOutOfPower","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I use Dragon Ascending during the Gather Power Phase, who becomes the First Player?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. You and another player will be tied for most Power, so the previous First Player will make that decision.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIUseDragonAscendingDuringTheGatherPowerPhaseWhoBecomesTheFirstPlayer","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. To Awaken an Independent Great Old One, you need a Controlled Gate and your own Great Old One. Does Yog-Sothoth, by himself, fulfill both these requirements?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, because Yog-Sothoth is not technically a Controlled Gate","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qToAwakenAnIndependentGreatOldOneYouNeedAControlledGateAndYourOwnGreatOldOneDoesYogSothothByHimselfFulfillBothTheseRequirements","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Chaugnar Faugn’s Miri Nigri ability gives Gates 3 Combat dice. Does this apply to Yog-Sothoth?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes! For example, if there are 4 Enemy Faction Great Old Ones on the Map and Opener Controlled Chaugnar Faugn, then Yog-Sothoth’s Combat would be 11 (8 + 3). However, if Opener also Controlled a normal Gate in the same Area as Yog-Sothoth, you would still only add 3, and not 6, to your Combat in that Area. The ability reads “in an Area,” which means that you get the Combat bonus once per Area rather than once per Gate.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qChaugnarFaugnsMiriNigriAbilityGivesGates3CombatDiceDoesThisApplyToYogSothoth","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If I move into 2 Areas for my “You have Units in at least 2 Areas containing enemy-controlled Gates” Spellbook, and one of those Units is moving Yog into a Lord’s Shadow Area, do I get my associated Spellbook?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. By Yog existing in an Area with a Lord’s Shadow, he overrides control, so it is no longer an enemy-Controlled Gate by virtue of Yog being in that Area.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIMoveInto2AreasForMyYouHaveUnitsInAtLeast2AreasContainingEnemyControlledGatesSpellbookAndOneOfThoseUnitsIsMovingYogIntoALordsShadowAreaDoIGetMyAssociatedSpellbook","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Sleeper uses Cursed Slumber to remove a Gate from the Map, does that lower the count towards Opener’s two Spellbooks requiring 8 or 12 Gates to exist on the Map, respectively?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, it lowers the count. A Gate on Sleeper’s Faction Card is not on the Map.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfSleeperUsesCursedSlumberToRemoveAGateFromTheMapDoesThatLowerTheCountTowardsOpenersTwoSpellbooksRequiring8Or12GatesToExistOnTheMapRespectively","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Sleeper use Cursed Slumber to place a Gate from his Faction Card onto the Area containing Yog-Sothoth, but lacking a normal Gate?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanSleeperUseCursedSlumberToPlaceAGateFromHisFactionCardOntoTheAreaContainingYogSothothButLackingANormalGate","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I have Energy Nexus and 0 Power, can I still do an Action that Costs 0 (or Hibernating, via Ancient Sorcery)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes! Using Energy Nexus does not require it to be your turn, so the rule that your turn is skipped when at 0 Power (or Hibernating) doesn’t apply.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIHaveEnergyNexusAnd0PowerCanIStillDoAnActionThatCosts0OrHibernatingViaAncientSorcery","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If my Serpent Man returns to the Map during the Doom Phase (Ancient Sorcery) to an Area with Windwalker’s Ice Age token, do I pay 1 Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, because returning the Serpent Man is not an Action—it occurs during the Doom Phase.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfMySerpentManReturnsToTheMapDuringTheDoomPhaseAncientSorceryToAnAreaWithWindwalkersIceAgeTokenDoIPay1Power","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Demand Sacrifice interact with the Leng Spider’s Bloodthirst?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Any Pains converted into Kills become single Pains. I recommend against using Bloodthirst!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoesDemandSacrificeInteractWithTheLengSpidersBloodthirst","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can I use Lethargy forever, thus preventing the game from ending?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. We recommend defenestration as the quickest way of managing such a player. More seriously, Sleeper cannot use Lethargy if no one else is active; just go ahead and finish out the Action Phase.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIUseLethargyForeverThusPreventingTheGameFromEnding","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Ancient Sorcery affect Great Cthulhu or Yellow Sign?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Ancient Sorcery doesn’t affect the targeted Faction at all. However, I think what you mean is, “how does Sleeper benefit from using Ancient Sorcery on Great Cthulhu or Yellow Sign?” The answer in the first case is that a unique ability that names a specific Great Old One allows Sleeper to apply that ability to Tsathoggua. Thus, if Ancient Sorcery affects Great Cthulhu, Sleeper can re-Awaken Tsathoggua for 4 Power (and will also earn 1 Elder Sign). With regards to Yellow Sign, during the Gather Power Phase, Sleeper will gain 1 Power for each Area containing one or more of his Units plus a Desecration token (which, admittedly, had to be created by Yellow Sign).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoesAncientSorceryAffectGreatCthulhuOrYellowSign","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If a Serpent Man uses Ancient Sorcery on Crawling Chaos, thus giving Sleeper the Flight ability, can this be combined with the Burrow Spellbook?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. Sleeper’s Units are able to fly while burrowing. Tsathoggua is not from this part of the universe.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfASerpentManUsesAncientSorceryOnCrawlingChaosThusGivingSleeperTheFlightAbilityCanThisBeCombinedWithTheBurrowSpellbook","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What does it mean that an Action must originate in the Battle Area when using Energy Nexus?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. It means that the Action, if tied to Map Areas, must begin in those Areas. For example, you can only use it to Move OUT of the Area (Burrow would apply), and not into it. You could only use Ancient Sorcery if the Serpent Man comes from that Area. You could Recruit, Summon, Awaken, or Capture a Unit in that Area. In a multi-Area situation, such as using Mother Hydra’s Zygote Action, then at least one Recruited Cultist must be placed in that Area. If it is not tied to a Map Area, then you may do it (such as one of Sleeper’s Spellbook requirements that is an Action). You could even do Lethargy if you wanted, but that really wouldn’t make much sense from a strategic standpoint.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhatDoesItMeanThatAnActionMustOriginateInTheBattleAreaWhenUsingEnergyNexus","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can I do the Battle Action with Energy Nexus?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. This results in an immediate Battle with you as the Attacker, which would be followed by the already-declared Battle, between whatever Units remain. You can only do 2 total Battles in a row (i.e., you cannot use Energy Nexus to “chain” Battles together into an infinite loop). However, you could use Energy Nexus to perform a non-Battle Action before the Energy Nexus Battle, which will happen before the Battle that was originally declared.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIDoTheBattleActionWithEnergyNexus","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can I use Energy Nexus even if the Battle in the Area was not declared against me (or by me)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Energy Nexus simply requires a Battle to be declared in the same Area as your Wizard. For example, if two other Factions Battled in an Area containing your Wizard, Sleeper could immediately Recruit a Cultist. If all the Units involved in the Battle were Killed and/or Pained, then Sleeper could take Control of an abandoned Gate on his turn without having to use his next turn’s Action to Recruit a Cultist there!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIUseEnergyNexusEvenIfTheBattleInTheAreaWasNotDeclaredAgainstMeOrByMe","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can I perform Unlimited Actions in addition to my one Action when using Energy Nexus?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. You may Abandon and/or Control a Gate in addition to your 1 Action, but may not do Unlimited Battle (one regular Battle is okay).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIPerformUnlimitedActionsInAdditionToMyOneActionWhenUsingEnergyNexus","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Do Battle abilities still apply if Energy Nexus removes all Units of one side so that a Battle does not really take place? For example, what if a single Monster declares Battle on Sleeper, and Tsathoggua simply uses Energy Nexus to Capture the Monster? Or if Sleeper simply Moves all of his units out of the Area?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Although Energy Nexus takes place prior to Pre-Battle, follow the same rule as to what happens when all Units of a side are removed during Pre-Battle. The Battle ends, no dice are rolled, and no abilities (including Pre-Battle!) can be used. The Power is paid to initiate the Battle, but no Battle actually takes place!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoBattleAbilitiesStillApplyIfEnergyNexusRemovesAllUnitsOfOneSideSoThatABattleDoesNotReallyTakePlaceForExampleWhatIfASingleMonsterDeclaresBattleOnSleeperAndTsathogguaSimplyUsesEnergyNexusToCaptureTheMonsterOrIfSleeperSimplyMovesAllOfHisUnitsOutOfTheArea","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does Demand Sacrifice protect against Eliminations?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, it only protects against Kill results.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoesDemandSacrificeProtectAgainstEliminations","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does Tsathoggua have to be personally involved in a Battle to use Demand Sacrifice?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. So long as Tsathoggua is in play, Demand Sacrifice applies to all Battles against Sleeper’s Units.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoesTsathogguaHaveToBePersonallyInvolvedInABattleToUseDemandSacrifice","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can the Opener of the Way use They Break Through to Summon a Monster onto the Cursed Slumber Gate?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. The Gate and Cultist under Cursed Slumber are immune to Enemy abilities.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanTheOpenerOfTheWayUseTheyBreakThroughToSummonAMonsterOntoTheCursedSlumberGate","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Sleeper choose to Eliminate his Cultist on a Cursed Slumber Gate to satisfy losses inflicted by Ghroth (or any similar ability)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, but he doesn’t have to even if it is the only Cultist he has left (since it is protected from all enemy abilities). If he DOES choose to lose it, the Gate becomes Abandoned and now provides Power to all Factions. It can still later be returned to the Map by Sleeper for 1 Power.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanSleeperChooseToEliminateHisCultistOnACursedSlumberGateToSatisfyLossesInflictedByGhrothOrAnySimilarAbility","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If a Cursed Slumber Gate has a High Priest on it, can that High Priest be sacrificed for Power? If so, what happens to the Gate?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. The Gate becomes Abandoned, as described in the previous answer.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfACursedSlumberGateHasAHighPriestOnItCanThatHighPriestBeSacrificedForPowerIfSoWhatHappensToTheGate","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I have acquired the Ghast Neutral Monsters, how and when would I spawn them via Death from Below?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Since they cost 2 Power, they are 2-cost Monsters. You will only receive 1 Ghast per spawning, so it is usually preferable to get some other Monster with Death from Below.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIHaveAcquiredTheGhastNeutralMonstersHowAndWhenWouldISpawnThemViaDeathFromBelow","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Sleeper uses Cursed Slumber to remove a Gate from the Map, does that change the count towards Opener’s two Spellbooks that require 8 or 12 Gates to exist on the Map, respectively?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes, it lowers the count. A Gate on Sleeper’s Faction Card is not on the Map.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfSleeperUsesCursedSlumberToRemoveAGateFromTheMapDoesThatChangeTheCountTowardsOpenersTwoSpellbooksThatRequire8Or12GatesToExistOnTheMapRespectively","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I Move a single Shantak who brings along a Cultist (using the Horror Steed ability), does Burrow give me a refund of 1 Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. Burrow gives you a refund based on spending 2 or more Power during a Move Action, not on Moving 2 or more Units. In this situation, you would have to pay to Move at least one more Unit to benefit from Burrow.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIMoveASingleShantakWhoBringsAlongACultistUsingTheHorrorSteedAbilityDoesBurrowGiveMeARefundOf1Power","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Can Sleeper perform a Ritual of Annihilation if he copied Eternal Servitude via Ancient Sorcery?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. The effects of Ancient Sorcery last until the end of the Doom Phase. This means that during Sleeper’s Doom Phase turn,\nthey would be unable to perform a Ritual. If Sleeper tasted the forbidden fruit of unlimited Power they must pay the price.\nHigh Priests, Dark Demon, and Brain Cylinders","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanSleeperPerformARitualOfAnnihilationIfHeCopiedEternalServitudeViaAncientSorcery","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Soulless interact with Gla’aki’s Green Decay and the Yithian’s Possession abilities?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Soulless makes the base reward 0 Power. Gla’aki’s Green Decay modifies that reward to be an Elder Sign (meaning that it overrides Soulless, by changing its reward from Power to an Elder Sign). The Yithian’s Possession adds to whatever the base reward is (whether 1, 0, or an Elder Sign). Thus, a Yithian who Captured a Soulless Tcho-Tcho still provides at least 1 Power.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoesSoullessInteractWithGlaakisGreenDecayAndTheYithiansPossessionAbilities","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What if the Tcho-Tcho has no Controlled Gate when you have the Hierophants Spellbook, and you earn another Spellbook?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Place the High Priest anywhere on the Map where you have Units. If you don’t have Units, place it anywhere on the Map. You’re probably going to lose this game.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhatIfTheTchoTchoHasNoControlledGateWhenYouHaveTheHierophantsSpellbookAndYouEarnAnotherSpellbook","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. In an 8 player game, it seems like the Tcho-Tcho are forced to appear in one of Windwalker’s start Areas. Is this really so?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yep.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qInAn8PlayerGameItSeemsLikeTheTchoTchoAreForcedToAppearInOneOfWindwalkersStartAreasIsThisReallySo","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When performing the Spellbook requirement of “Remove my Controlled Gate in my Start Area,” can I remove Yog-Sothoth?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Of course not. He is not your Controlled Gate.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhenPerformingTheSpellbookRequirementOfRemoveMyControlledGateInMyStartAreaCanIRemoveYogSothoth","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I control Yig as the Tcho-Tchos, and perform Yig’s Spellbook requirement of “Remove one of my Controlled Gates” can this count as my own Spellbook requirement of “Remove my Controlled Gate...” or vice versa?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. They must be two separate removals. One per Spellbook.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIControlYigAsTheTchoTchosAndPerformYigsSpellbookRequirementOfRemoveOneOfMyControlledGatesCanThisCountAsMyOwnSpellbookRequirementOfRemoveMyControlledGateOrViceVersa","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Do I benefit from Martyrdom if my High Priest is Eliminated in Battle (such as by being Abducted or Devoured), but not actually Killed?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. Martyrdom only takes effect if the High Priest is actually Killed.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoIBenefitFromMartyrdomIfMyHighPriestIsEliminatedInBattleSuchAsByBeingAbductedOrDevouredButNotActuallyKilled","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Give me an example of how Tablets of the Gods works.","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. If the Tcho-Tcho have this Spellbook and perform a Ritual of Annihilation, then they MUST Eliminate all of their High Priests, even those who do not qualify for Elder Signs. Their only element of choice in the matter is whether or not they perform the Ritual. They could sacrifice their High Priests for the Power reward, and then do the Ritual.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qGiveMeAnExampleOfHowTabletsOfTheGodsWorks","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can I use Terror to have some of my Proto-Shoggoths reduce enemy combat, while the rest roll 2 dice each?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. All Proto-Shoggoths must “vibrate” in the same way, so if you have 4 in an Area, you can either roll 8 dice, OR roll 4 dice and subtract 4 from the enemy dice total; no Mister In-Between. (and if the enemy’s reduction goes to below 0, he still just rolls 0. No negative Combat ratings!)","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIUseTerrorToHaveSomeOfMyProtoShoggothsReduceEnemyCombatWhileTheRestRoll2DiceEach","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If the Tcho-Tcho Recruit a Unique High Priest, are they affected by the various abilities of the Tcho-Tcho regarding High Priests (Hierophants, Martyrdom, Tablets, etc.) and can they be used to Awaken Ubbo-Sathla?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes to all—the Unique High Priest acts as your other two “regular” High Priests in every way, EXCEPT that it cannot use the normal Unspeakable Oath ability. High Priests can only use the abilities on their own Loyalty Cards.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfTheTchoTchoRecruitAUniqueHighPriestAreTheyAffectedByTheVariousAbilitiesOfTheTchoTchoRegardingHighPriestsHierophantsMartyrdomTabletsEtcAndCanTheyBeUsedToAwakenUbboSathla","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: How does Sycophancy interact with Sleeper while using Ancient Sorcery?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Because the Tcho-Tcho Sycophancy unique ability applies to the entire Doom Phase, Sleeper can use Ancient Sorcery to gain its benefit throughout that Phase. In such a case, return the Serpent Man to the Map at the very end of the Doom Phase, rather then when it is Sleeper’s turn to perform a Ritual, which is normally when you use abilities in the Doom Phase.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoesSycophancyInteractWithSleeperWhileUsingAncientSorcery","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. With the Hierophants Spellbook, do the Tcho-Tcho get to place a free High Priest when they earn an Independent Great Old One’s Spellbook, too?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, that is not the intent. It reads “Faction Spellbooks.” Otherwise it would be too gross.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWithTheHierophantsSpellbookDoTheTchoTchoGetToPlaceAFreeHighPriestWhenTheyEarnAnIndependentGreatOldOnesSpellbookToo","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Ithaqua is Awakened in an Area with a Lord’s Shadow (that also has a Windwalker Glyph, obviously), what\nhappens?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Windwalker gets to choose the Gate that is destroyed in the Area (the normal Gate or the Lord’s Shadow). If the choice is\nbetween Yog-Sothoth and a Lord’s Shadow, then they must destroy the Lord’s Shadow instead of Yog.\n","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIthaquaIsAwakenedInAnAreaWithALordsShadowThatAlsoHasAWindwalkerGlyphObviouslyWhatHappens","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If I have no Units and/or had no Captured Cultist(s) on my Faction Card, and effectively only have Baphomet\nout, do I still get an Elder Sign if unable to pay these apparent costs for Sacrament of Flesh?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Yes. Just rest assured that Baphomet is extracting this toll from someone else, in another part of the universe, tenfold. You still\nget the Elder Sign(s). If your opponents had you down to just Baphomet in play (it happens), they should have finished the job\nand Killed him too.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIHaveNoUnitsAndOrHadNoCapturedCultistSOnMyFactionCardAndEffectivelyOnlyHaveBaphometOutDoIStillGetAnElderSignIfUnableToPayTheseApparentCostsForSacramentOfFlesh","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If I spend any amount of Power during my turn that gets me to 0 Power, can I continue to spend “virtual”\nPower that Eternal Servitude provides?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: You cannot spend real and the “virtual” Power that Eternal Servitude provides in the same Action Phase unless some effect\ngives them real Power after they use their “virtual” Power from Eternal Servitude. The “check” for Eternal Servitude is at the\nbeginning of your turn, before you can take Actions. Therefore, being at 1 Power is usually worse (but not always) than being at\n0 Power.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfISpendAnyAmountOfPowerDuringMyTurnThatGetsMeTo0PowerCanIContinueToSpendVirtualPowerThatEternalServitudeProvides","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: With Unlimited Battle, can I spend 2 “virtual” Power and then attack with Baphomet by spending 1 Doom all\nwithin the same Action Phase?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Yes. And if Baphomet is Pained into another Area (provided you have 6 Spellbooks), you may attack again, and again, by\npaying 1 Doom per Battle per normal Unlimited Combat Rules.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWithUnlimitedBattleCanISpend2VirtualPowerAndThenAttackWithBaphometBySpending1DoomAllWithinTheSameActionPhase","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: What is meant by “active” in Eternal Servitude?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: In this case, “active” refers to a player that isn’t Hibernating or has more than 0 Power. This always means that The Invasion\nget the “second-to-last word” of any Action Phase, since the last player who takes the last Action will prevent you from being able\nto trigger Eternal Servitude again.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhatIsMeantByActiveInEternalServitude","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Can I Awaken Baphomet if I’m at 0 Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. If you are at 0 Power and do not have Baphomet in play, then you’re just like any other Faction when they are at 0\nPower, and cannot take any Actions during your turn, even if those Actions cost 0 Power. Killing Baphomet when The Invasion\nis at 0 Power is an effective way to cripple them.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIAwakenBaphometIfImAt0Power","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Can Sleeper use Lethargy endlessly to give The Invasion infinite usage of Eternal Servitude?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. If nobody but Sleeper has Power, Sleeper may not continue to use Lethargy, as per the Final Onslaught Rulebook FAQ.\n","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanSleeperUseLethargyEndlesslyToGiveTheInvasionInfiniteUsageOfEternalServitude","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If Sleeper is copying Eternal Servitude and has a High Priest, can you use the “virtual” two Power of Eternal\nServitude first, and then sacrifice his High Priest for 2 Power and then spend that Power to take additional Actions?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Yes, but not the other way around. He couldn’t have 2 (or more) Power and then use Eternal Servitude Power in the same\nAction Phase. The “check” for getting to access Eternal Servitude’s “virtual” Power is at the beginning of your turn, before you\ndo—or can do—any specific Actions (of any kind).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfSleeperIsCopyingEternalServitudeAndHasAHighPriestCanYouUseTheVirtualTwoPowerOfEternalServitudeFirstAndThenSacrificeHisHighPriestFor2PowerAndThenSpendThatPowerToTakeAdditionalActions","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If Sleeper copies Eternal Servitude and Windwalker’s Hibernate, can they Hibernate for 4 Power from 0 Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. Even though you are doing Actions as if you had 2 Power with Eternal Servitude, you never actually had Power during\nyour turn. Hibernate would do you nothing here.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfSleeperCopiesEternalServitudeAndWindwalkersHibernateCanTheyHibernateFor4PowerFrom0Power","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If Sleeper is copying Eternal Servitude and wants to use Energy Nexus in a Battle, when Sleeper is at 0 Power,\ncan he do another Action per Energy Nexus?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Yes and no. If Sleeper is Attacking, then he would have spent 1 “virtual” Power to Attack, and therefore would have another\n“virtual” Power available via Eternal Servitude. However, if he was defending, he wouldn’t have access to Eternal Servitude’s\nbenefits (because it’s not his turn).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfSleeperIsCopyingEternalServitudeAndWantsToUseEnergyNexusInABattleWhenSleeperIsAt0PowerCanHeDoAnotherActionPerEnergyNexus","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Can I contribute two Power via Eternal Servitude to preventing Crawling Chaos from getting Power from\nThousand Forms while I’m at 0 Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No, you are at 0 Power. You have no Power to give. Eternal Servitude doesn’t give you Power; it just allows you to conduct\nActions as if you had 2 Power, and only during your turn, anyway.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIContributeTwoPowerViaEternalServitudeToPreventingCrawlingChaosFromGettingPowerFromThousandFormsWhileImAt0Power","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: When moving off of the Moon with Eternal Servitude, does Bubastis get Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No, as no Power was actually spent. However, Catnapping against The Invasion is still incredibly good; if they “trickle” their\nUnits back onto the board from the Moon, they are likely to be easily picked apart by everyone.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhenMovingOffOfTheMoonWithEternalServitudeDoesBubastisGetPower","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Does earning Doom from Blood Offering earn you a Spellbook like “Gain an Elder Sign” for Tcho-Tcho?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. Upon an agreed “deal,” Blood Offering discards the Elder Sign, giving the deal-making player Doom equal to their total\nvalue. The Elder Sign itself never goes into their hands, nor is it even touched by that player.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoesEarningDoomFromBloodOfferingEarnYouASpellbookLikeGainAnElderSignForTchoTcho","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Does Blood Offering trigger Infernolatreia?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. Infernolatreia only triggers when you earn Elder Signs. There is no way to give Elder Signs to anyone involved using\nBlood Offering—you are looking at them to potentially give the Doom value to your opponents.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoesBloodOfferingTriggerInfernolatreia","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Does Blood Offering trigger Passion?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoesBloodOfferingTriggerPassion","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Can a deal be struck where you can acquire Cultists but not exchange any Doom from the revealed Elder Signs,\nor vice-versa?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. One Elder Sign’s value must be exchanged, and one Cultist be exchanged, to strike a deal.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanADealBeStruckWhereYouCanAcquireCultistsButNotExchangeAnyDoomFromTheRevealedElderSignsOrViceVersa","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Does Blood Offering trigger the Baphomet’s Fury’s Torment OR Transference ability, since they are not\ntechnically “Captures”?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. Treat them as if they were Captured normally; Torment already has an exception for this as well as Transference.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoesBloodOfferingTriggerTheBaphometsFurysTormentOrTransferenceAbilitySinceTheyAreNotTechnicallyCaptures","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If there are 3 created Lord’s Shadows in play and I gain 2 Elder Signs, what happens?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: If an effect gives you 2 Elder Signs at one time (like Sacrament of Flesh does when you have 6 Spellbooks), then you’d look at 4 Elder Signs (if you had 3 Lord’s Shadows) and keep 2 of them.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfThereAre3CreatedLordsShadowsInPlayAndIGain2ElderSignsWhatHappens","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Scavenge is considered “one Action.” What does that mean?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: It means that it cannot be responded to by abilities like Unspeakable Oath (if playing with High Priests) or Great Cthulhu’s\nDevolve. Additionally, it means that it doesn’t transfer Baphomet’s Fury more than once per Scavenge activation. If you Killed or were Killed by multiple enemies at the end of any use of Scavenge, then choose which eligible player would receive it.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qScavengeIsConsideredOneActionWhatDoesThatMean","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Can you Attack and Capture in the same Area with one use of Scavenge?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanYouAttackAndCaptureInTheSameAreaWithOneUseOfScavenge","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If you use Scavenge in an Area where Baphomet is, to Attack or Capture there, what happens? Do you pay 1\nDoom per Unquenchable Thirst?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: You aren’t declaring Battle/Capture with Baphomet, and he’s not in the Combat, so you don’t pay 1 Doom. It’s technically not disabling or deactivating the ability, since Baphomet is not involved.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfYouUseScavengeInAnAreaWhereBaphometIsToAttackOrCaptureThereWhatHappensDoYouPay1DoomPerUnquenchableThirst","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Can I use Hellgate and Attack with Unlimited Battle in the same Action Phase?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Yes. And you can do so when you’re at 0 Power with Eternal Servitude + Unquenchable Thirst, as the total cost of those Actions is 2 Power and 1 Doom.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanIUseHellgateAndAttackWithUnlimitedBattleInTheSameActionPhase","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If a player hits 30 Doom during the Doom Phase, does Entropy Siphon still trigger?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Yes. Even if the result of that would bring them below 30 Doom, the endgame still triggered, so whoever had the most Doom at the end of the phase would still win. This may lead to ties slightly more often if the players in the lead can’t (or won’t) pay the 4 Power per Fiend-Controlled Gate.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfAPlayerHits30DoomDuringTheDoomPhaseDoesEntropySiphonStillTrigger","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If I have a Fiend-Controlled Gate in an Area with a created Lord’s Shadow, do I get 2 “triggers” of Entropy\nSiphon from that Fiend, draining enemies ahead of me of either 8 Power or 2 Doom?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. The Lord’s Shadow is always either Controlled by you, or by another player if THEY have a Controlled Gate in the Area. Since another player does not have a Controlled Gate in the Area, you are Controlling it by default (without a Controlling Unit). You still get to trigger Entropy Siphon once in this situation, though (for the normal Gate).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIHaveAFiendControlledGateInAnAreaWithACreatedLordsShadowDoIGet2TriggersOfEntropySiphonFromThatFiendDrainingEnemiesAheadOfMeOfEither8PowerOr2Doom","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: What happens in the second Doom Phase when I trigger my Spellbook requirements “At the end of the Second\nDoom Phase take this Spellbook. All other players lose 1 Doom,” and “Entropy Siphon” at the same time?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: You choose the order of how they trigger. Best to optimize the order of these for maximum damage.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhatHappensInTheSecondDoomPhaseWhenITriggerMySpellbookRequirementsAtTheEndOfTheSecondDoomPhaseTakeThisSpellbookAllOtherPlayersLose1DoomAndEntropySiphonAtTheSameTime","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If (for example) The Invasion have 20 Doom and an opponent has 21 Doom, and there are two Fiend-\nControlled Gates, what happens?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Each instance of Entropy Siphon triggers separately. The end effect is that your Doom can never be lowered below what The Invasion’s Doom is, regardless if there are 1 or even 4 Fiend-Controlled Gates.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfForExampleTheInvasionHave20DoomAndAnOpponentHas21DoomAndThereAreTwoFiendControlledGatesWhatHappens","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Does Yog Count as a Controlled Gate for the purposes of Eclipse?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. He is not “Unit-Controlled” as Eclipse specifies.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoesYogCountAsAControlledGateForThePurposesOfEclipse","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Does the Moon count as a Controlled Gate for the purposes of Eclipse?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: No. Eclipse only targets Gates with a Controlling Unit.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoesTheMoonCountAsAControlledGateForThePurposesOfEclipse","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If Thousand Forms is triggered and The Invasion would want to give up 1 Power but another player wants to\ngive up Power to prevent The Invasion from giving up that 1 Power, what happens?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: If the agreement amongst players that have Power to contribute to Thousand Forms is not a consensus, then Crawling Chaos\ngets the Power rolled. This is a situation that only ever would happen if Invasion was in the game, so we included it here.\nBaphomet’s Combat","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfThousandFormsIsTriggeredAndTheInvasionWouldWantToGiveUp1PowerButAnotherPlayerWantsToGiveUpPowerToPreventTheInvasionFromGivingUpThat1PowerWhatHappens","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: How does Baphomet’s Combat value work?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: You can reveal Elder Signs at any time during the game—between, before, or during any Action or during any phase. This\nmeans you can reveal Elder Signs after being Attacked, and even after Pre-Battle to boost Baphomet’s Combat value. This has\nweird interactions as well, like if fighting Ithaqua, you’ll be boosting him too (but only by half ) when you’re revealing Elder\nSigns.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoesBaphometsCombatValueWork","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If I reveal 7 value worth of Elder Signs, gain 7 Doom, and then spend 1 Doom to Attack with Baphomet, do I\nadd the 7 to his 4 Combat, or would I add 6 to his Combat because I “spent” one?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Just because you spent Doom from those Elder Signs doesn’t mean that you didn’t earn it. It’s “gross” Doom, not “net” Doom. We recommend just leaving these near your Faction Card for the remainder of the Action Phase until they no longer have any further effect.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIReveal7ValueWorthOfElderSignsGain7DoomAndThenSpend1DoomToAttackWithBaphometDoIAddThe7ToHis4CombatOrWouldIAdd6ToHisCombatBecauseISpentOne","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: How does Torment work? This is very confusing.","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: If Great Cthulhu had Baphomet’s Fury and faux “Killed” a Unit, but it remained in play (as per Torment) then he wouldn’t\nreceive his “Kill/Devour a Unit in Battle” Spellbook(s), as no Unit was actually Killed or Devoured.
\nA: If Opener had Units “Killed” via Torment, they would be able to “upgrade” with Million Favored Ones.\nA: If Crawling Chaos had Baphomet’s Fury and was to Kill an enemy Great Old One, it wouldn’t trigger Harbinger, as that\nUnit never was Killed or Eliminated because of the replacement effect of Torment.
\nA: Any Unit Killed/Eliminated pre-battle, like being Devoured by Cthulhu while Great Cthulhu has the Baphomet’s Fury,\nwould stay in play for the rest of the Battle (provided that the Power could be afforded during Pre-Battle to keep that Unit\nalive). Keep in mind that you calculate/resolve Torment whenever an effect happens, not at the end of an Action. This means that\nUnits could be “spared” during Pre-Battle only to be later lost during Combat resolution if they don’t have the Power to cover\nthose costs. In this way as well, Units can somewhat absorb multiple “Deaths” during a Battle, as those are prevented by Torment\n(provided those are caused by Pre-Battle abilities). Torment does not change that Units (other than Starspawn) can only absorb 1\nCombat result.
\nA: Windwalker’s Cannibalism wouldn’t trigger if Torment prevented the Kills in an Area.
\nA: Torment is not a Battle ability and also affects things like Ghroth and Dread Curse. This is not always a penalty and can be\nused in clever ways to degrade your opponents.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoesTormentWorkThisIsVeryConfusing","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: The Invasion don’t have a High Priest, Brain Cylinder, or Dark Demon model(s). What am I supposed to do if playing with these expansions?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Dark Demon: When Dark Demon is triggered by someone else, you will permanently lose a Larvae, although you won’t receive a Dark Demon. If you purchase Dark Demon, everyone else follows the instructions for Dark Demon and you get nothing in return. Seeing as Dark Demons are rather annoying to be cursed with, this is actually a decent exchange for you.
A: High Priests: When opponents sacrifice a High Priest via Unspeakable Oath, it is in turn-order response to whatever Action\njust occurred. Often times, this means that The Invasion player will get yet another use of Eternal Servitude when High Priests\nare in use, if they are between the player who performed the last Action and whoever is now “reinstated” into the Action Phase\nwith 2 power. This is important and means The Invasion benefits from High Priests immensely, even though they themselves\ncannot have one.
A: Brain Cylinders: The Invasion has no Brain Cylinders and therefore gets no benefit for Controlling the Lab, other than\npreventing other players from being able to trigger Surgery. Don’t worry though; Brain Cylinders are typically easy to capture and\nare great targets via Scavenge, so you’ll have more “food” for Baphomet in those situations. Also, other players will typically have\nmore Power, so that’s even more opportunity to use Eternal Servitude.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qTheInvasionDontHaveAHighPriestBrainCylinderOrDarkDemonModelSWhatAmISupposedToDoIfPlayingWithTheseExpansions","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Windwalker’s Hibernate interact with Crawling Chaos’ Thousand Forms?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Despite the fact that Windwalker is not an active Faction when Hibernating, he does participate in the negotiations for how much Power is lost, and he may choose to lose Power due to Thousand Forms.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoesWindwalkersHibernateInteractWithCrawlingChaosThousandForms","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Normally, when a Faction with 0 Power somehow gains new Power, it re-enters the Action Phase sequence. What happens if Windwalker under Hibernation gains Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. You gain the Power, but remain under the effects of  Hibernation and may take no Actions. You may only spend Power when given the option via Spellbooks or abilities. For example, Rhan Tegoth’s Eternal ability can keep him from being Killed or Pained.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qNormallyWhenAFactionWith0PowerSomehowGainsNewPowerItReEntersTheActionPhaseSequenceWhatHappensIfWindwalkerUnderHibernationGainsPower","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Gnoph-Keh cost depends on the number of Gnoph-Kehs in the Pool. Please give a precise breakdown.","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. If no Gnoph-Kehs are on the Map, Summoning one costs 4 Power. With one on the Map (and three in the Pool), the cost is 3. With two each in the Pool and on the Map, the third will cost 2, and the final Gnoph-Keh will only cost 1. Remember that a Gnoph-Keh Captured by Tsathoggua is not in the Pool, and thus decreases the cost for future Summons!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qGnophKehCostDependsOnTheNumberOfGnophKehsInThePoolPleaseGiveAPreciseBreakdown","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I have no Wendigos in my Pool, and one is Killed in Battle, can I immediately re-spawn it via Cannibalism (assuming I’d Killed an Enemy Unit in that same Battle)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. Obnoxious, eh? It also works with Cultists.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfIHaveNoWendigosInMyPoolAndOneIsKilledInBattleCanIImmediatelyReSpawnItViaCannibalismAssumingIdKilledAnEnemyUnitInThatSameBattle","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Cannibalism is used in a Battle, immediately followed by Black Goat’s Necrophagy, could the newly placed Acolyte or Wendigo be Pained out?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, because that particular Acolyte or Wendigo did not participate in the Battle.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfCannibalismIsUsedInABattleImmediatelyFollowedByBlackGoatsNecrophagyCouldTheNewlyPlacedAcolyteOrWendigoBePainedOut","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Rhan Tegoth’s Eternal ability interact with abilities such as Nyarlathotep’s Harbinger or Cthulhu’s Spellbook requirement that must be fulfilled with a Kill?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Rhan Tegoth’s Eternal ability only cancels the effect of a Kill or Pain on Rhan Tegoth itself, not the effect such a result has on other abilities and Spellbooks. In other words, Nyarlathotep can gain Power or Elder Signs and Cthulhu can earn a Spellbook when the result is assigned to Rhan Tegoth, even when Eternal is used to cancel the effect.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoesRhanTegothsEternalAbilityInteractWithAbilitiesSuchAsNyarlathotepsHarbingerOrCthulhusSpellbookRequirementThatMustBeFulfilledWithAKill","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Cthugha rolls a Kill on Rhan Tegoth, but the latter uses Eternal to cancel it, does Cthugha still have a chance to spare Rhan Tegoth, too?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, Eternal takes precedence—if Windwalker chooses to remove the Kill or Pain from Rhan Tegoth, Cthugha cannot spare him.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfCthughaRollsAKillOnRhanTegothButTheLatterUsesEternalToCancelItDoesCthughaStillHaveAChanceToSpareRhanTegothToo","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What does it mean in the description of Ice Age when it refers to “any Action ending in the Ice Age Area”?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. This describes any Actions involving Units that finish their turn in the Area, or that do something to the Area itself. For example, Units can Move OUT of the Area for no extra cost. But moving INTO the Area costs an additional Power (not per Unit, just for the entire Move Action). For other examples, if Yellow Sign tried to Desecrate the Area, it would cost one additional Power. If Cthulhu emerged from Submerge in the Ice Age Area, he would pay one additional Power (but not if he left the Area via Submerge). Great Cthulhu’s Devolve is not an Action, so it is still free, though using Dreams would cost him three Power. Black Goat’s Avatar would cost one additional Power as at least one Unit will be ending that Action in that Area (even if the Unit ending up in that Area is not a Black Goat Unit). Opener of the Way’s Units can Promote after Battle and Sleeper can use Death From Below in the Ice Age Area free of cost, as these are not Actions. If Sleeper declares Lethargy while Tsathoggua is in the Ice Age Area, it costs one Power. If you use a multiple-Area Action, such as if you used Mother Hydra’s Zygote, and placed at least one Recruited Cultist there, it would cost an additional Power.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhatDoesItMeanInTheDescriptionOfIceAgeWhenItRefersToAnyActionEndingInTheIceAgeArea","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Controlling or Abandoning a Gate is defined in the rules as an Unlimited Action that costs 0 Power. Does this mean it costs 1 Power to Control or Abandon a Gate if the Ice Age marker is in the Area?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. These are the only two Actions (Controlling a Gate and Abandoning a Gate) exempted from Ice Age’s Power tax. Unlimited Battle still costs +1 Power to initiate.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qControllingOrAbandoningAGateIsDefinedInTheRulesAsAnUnlimitedActionThatCosts0PowerDoesThisMeanItCosts1PowerToControlOrAbandonAGateIfTheIceAgeMarkerIsInTheArea","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Crawling Chaos Units fly over (but not land in) an Ice Age Area without spending extra Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. They are not ending their Action in that Area!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanCrawlingChaosUnitsFlyOverButNotLandInAnIceAgeAreaWithoutSpendingExtraPower","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Yog-Sothoth is in the Area in which you Awaken Ithaqua, can Yog-Sothoth be the Gate you replace with Ithaqua?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. If Yog-Sothoth is the only Gate in the Area, then yes. If there is another available Gate, then you must replace THAT Gate with Ithaqua instead.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfYogSothothIsInTheAreaInWhichYouAwakenIthaquaCanYogSothothBeTheGateYouReplaceWithIthaqua","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Who determines where a Unit is Retreated to when Howl is used?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. The victim decides which Unit is Retreated, and to which adjacent Area it goes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qWhoDeterminesWhereAUnitIsRetreatedToWhenHowlIsUsed","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Windwalker’s Units completely surround an Area before a Battle, and Windwalker uses Howl, is the Retreated Unit Killed (as per the rule that surrounded Units must receive an extra Elimination if they cannot be Pained)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. It may retreat to an Area containing Units, because Howl does not inflict a Pain.Windwalker’s ","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfWindwalkersUnitsCompletelySurroundAnAreaBeforeABattleAndWindwalkerUsesHowlIsTheRetreatedUnitKilledAsPerTheRuleThatSurroundedUnitsMustReceiveAnExtraEliminationIfTheyCannotBePained","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Units retreated due to Howl still use Battle Abilities that have not yet been activated (such as promoting Units via Million Favored Ones, or Nyarlathotep’s Harbinger)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No, they do not participate in the rest of the Battle, and so cannot use their Abilities.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanUnitsRetreatedDueToHowlStillUseBattleAbilitiesThatHaveNotYetBeenActivatedSuchAsPromotingUnitsViaMillionFavoredOnesOrNyarlathotepsHarbinger","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Howl be used on Map enemies such as Zoogs, Bhole, the Watcher, etc.?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Although Howl works on any Unit, rather than the typical specification of a Monster or Cultist, it does not work on the larger Map enemies such as the Bhole, Watcher, Librarian or Custodian. It would, however, work on Zoogs and uncontrolled Slimes. (In the former case, it Eliminates it but does not reflect a Pain back, and in the latter, you choose where the Slime is sent).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanHowlBeUsedOnMapEnemiesSuchAsZoogsBholeTheWatcherEtc","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does Crawling Chaos’ Madness ability allow him to choose the Area to which victims of Howl are retreated?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. Howl is a Retreat, not a Pain.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDoesCrawlingChaosMadnessAbilityAllowHimToChooseTheAreaToWhichVictimsOfHowlAreRetreated","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Windwalker’s Howl retreat a Brain Cylinder on the Yuggoth map?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. No. Brain Cylinders turn off their sensors, so they don’t hear the Howl.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanWindwalkersHowlRetreatABrainCylinderOnTheYuggothMap","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can a Ghoul that was forced to Retreat by Howl use Necrophagy to return to the Area (and add a Pain) after the Battle?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. The Ghoul did not participate in the Battle.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qCanAGhoulThatWasForcedToRetreatByHowlUseNecrophagyToReturnToTheAreaAndAddAPainAfterTheBattle","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. During the Action Phase, if a Player reveals his Elder Signs and causes the game to end, does Windwalker still get to fulfill his Spellbook requirement which states “Take this Spellbook at any time”?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes. Treat this Spellbook requirement similar to the way in which every player may reveal Elder Signs at the moment the game ends. This means that Windwalker could also immediately turn in all the Elder Signs he might receive from fulfilling that Spellbook requirement. No one said Windwalker played fair!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qDuringTheActionPhaseIfAPlayerRevealsHisElderSignsAndCausesTheGameToEndDoesWindwalkerStillGetToFulfillHisSpellbookRequirementWhichStatesTakeThisSpellbookAtAnyTime","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If one of Windwalker’s Gnoph-Keh has been captured by Sleeper via Capture Monster, how does this affect the Summoning cost of the next Gnoph-Keh?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. A Gnoph-Keh on Sleeper’s Faction Card is not considered to be in your Unit Pool. For example, if you had one Gnoph-Keh in play and one on Sleeper’s Faction Card, then the next Gnoph-Keh would cost 2 Power to Summon, because 2 are currently in your Unit Pool.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfOneOfWindwalkersGnophKehHasBeenCapturedBySleeperViaCaptureMonsterHowDoesThisAffectTheSummoningCostOfTheNextGnophKeh","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If you have Herald of the Outer Gods, do you still advance the Ritual of Annihilation marker up when paying the 5 Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfYouHaveHeraldOfTheOuterGodsDoYouStillAdvanceTheRitualOfAnnihilationMarkerUpWhenPayingThe5Power","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If Rhan-Tegoth is Attacked and dealt a Kill by the person holding the Baphomet’s Fury, what happens?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Windwalker can use Eternal to ignore the effect of the Kill by paying 1 Power. If they don’t, they pay 3 Power instead to ignore the Kill via Torment. If they have insufficient Power at that point, then Rhan would be Killed normally.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfRhanTegothIsAttackedAndDealtAKillByThePersonHoldingTheBaphometsFuryWhatHappens","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: If Rhan-Tegoth is Attacked and dealt a Kill by Nyarlathotep when Crawling Chaos is holding Baphomet’s Fury,\nwhat happens?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: Windwalker CAN choose to trigger Eternal by paying 1 Power OR they can choose to not trigger Eternal and allow Torment to trigger (provided they can pay for it). Here, Windwalker has an interesting decision: pay less Power but allow Harbinger to trigger, or pay more Power and prevent Harbinger from triggering by allowing Torment to take effect. It’s up to them. The general rule is that Torment is similar to Rhan-Tegoth’s Eternal ability; however, while Eternal ignores the effect of the Kill, Torment instead is a replacement effect that replaces Kills or Eliminations with Power loss (if they are able to pay).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qIfRhanTegothIsAttackedAndDealtAKillByNyarlathotepWhenCrawlingChaosIsHoldingBaphometsFuryWhatHappens","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: How does Ice Age interact with The Invasion’s abilities?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Factions","text":"A: You cannot enter an Area with Ice Age via Scavenge unless you are willing to pay 1 more Power, making it impossible once\nyou are on “virtual” Power via Eternal Servitude. If at 0 Power and using Eternal Servitude, you cannot move any Gryllusses\ninto any Area with the Ice Age marker via Scavenge.
\nA: Using Hellgate to enter an Ice Age Area would cost 1 more, so it likewise can’t be done with Eternal Servitude’s “virtual”\nPower.
\nA: Attacking or Capturing with Baphomet would cost 1 Power (in addition to one Doom via Unquenchable Thirst).
\nA: If an Ice Age is on an Area with a Lord’s Shadow, the cost is +1 to Portend. However, there are multiple costs for Portend. Whatever cost you would pay in any situation, just add +1 to it. For example, if they had 3 Demon Larvae in an Area and they were adding the third Portent in that Area, it would regularly cost 0. However, Ice Age makes it cost 1 more (so 1 total). If those same 3 Demon Larvae were trying to add a 4th Portent to the Area, it natively would cost 4 and Ice Age would make it cost 5 total.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-factions#qHowDoesIceAgeInteractWithTheInvasionsAbilities","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Undimensioned interact with unusual locations, such as Cthulhu’s Submerged Units, or Sleeper’s Gate with a Cultist that is in Cursed Slumber?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Spellbooks","text":"A. Undimensioned specifies that you may only rearrange Units among your Areas. So, you could not swap out a Cultist who is Cursed Slumbering with one from the Map, or change which Units are currently Submerged with Cthulhu, since these are not Areas. (When Cthulhu is Submerged he uses incalculable geometry such that even beings who are temporarily dimensionless cannot reach him).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-spellbooks#qHowDoesUndimensionedInteractWithUnusualLocationsSuchAsCthulhusSubmergedUnitsOrSleepersGateWithACultistThatIsInCursedSlumber","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Do Units from my Faction need to be involved in a Battle in order to use Shriveling?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Spellbooks","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-spellbooks#qDoUnitsFromMyFactionNeedToBeInvolvedInABattleInOrderToUseShriveling","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Shriveling is used on one of Black Goat’s Monsters, and Black Goat has the Spellbook Thousand Young, how much Power does Black Goat receive?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Spellbooks","text":"A. The Thousand Young Spellbook changes the cost of each of Black Goat’s Faction Monsters, so Shriveling would grant Black Goat the reduced cost to Summon. For example, Black Goat would receive 0 Power when a Ghoul is Shriveled.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-spellbooks#qIfShrivelingIsUsedOnOneOfBlackGoatsMonstersAndBlackGoatHasTheSpellbookThousandYoungHowMuchPowerDoesBlackGoatReceive","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How many points does the owner get when her Gnoph-Keh is Shriveled?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Spellbooks","text":"A. When a Gnoph-Keh is Shriveled, calculate the cost it would take to Summon it at that moment, not how much it would cost to re-Summon it. This means that if Windwalker had all four Gnoph-Keh on the board at the moment of Shriveling, it would grant him 0 Power.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-spellbooks#qHowManyPointsDoesTheOwnerGetWhenHerGnophKehIsShriveled","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Why is The Mao Ceremony worded cumbersomely, reading “after the minimum Power rule, but before Determine First Player”?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Spellbooks","text":"A. Because it is always the very last Power to be added—even after the minimum Power rule. This is the only ability in the game which must take place at that moment. To be clear, when Mao Ceremony is in play, first all players tally up their Power, then the minimum Power rule occurs, and finally Mao Ceremony can be used. (By the way, a High Priest can still be sacrificed for 2 Power at any time, Mao Ceremony notwithstanding).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-spellbooks#qWhyIsTheMaoCeremonyWordedCumbersomelyReadingAfterTheMinimumPowerRuleButBeforeDetermineFirstPlayer","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What does Recriminations mean when it says that you may replace a Spellbook with any available Spellbook?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Spellbooks","text":"A. You may replace the selected Spellbook with one of your own Faction Spellbooks or another Azathoth Spellbook from the Pool. You may NOT use Recriminations in conjunction with any Independent Great Old One Spellbooks—only with Spellbooks which can be placed on your Faction Card.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-spellbooks#qWhatDoesRecriminationsMeanWhenItSaysThatYouMayReplaceASpellbookWithAnyAvailableSpellbook","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I use Recriminations to remove another Neutral Spellbook from my Faction Card, does that Spellbook go back to the general Pool, where anyone can now earn it, or does it remain in my own, exclusive Spellbook Pool?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Spellbooks","text":"A. It goes back to the general, Neutral Spellbook Pool. If a Neutral Spellbook is not currently on your Faction Card, then any Faction may earn it.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-spellbooks#qIfIUseRecriminationsToRemoveAnotherNeutralSpellbookFromMyFactionCardDoesThatSpellbookGoBackToTheGeneralPoolWhereAnyoneCanNowEarnItOrDoesItRemainInMyOwnExclusiveSpellbookPool","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How many points does the owner get when her Ghast is Shriveled?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Spellbooks","text":"A. Two, since that’s how much a single Ghast costs to Summon.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-spellbooks#qHowManyPointsDoesTheOwnerGetWhenHerGhastIsShriveled","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What happens when you use Recriminations on a Spellbook that contains a Moonbeast?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Spellbooks","text":"A. The Moonbeast is removed with the Spellbook (costing nothing to do so) and follows normal rules for returning it to the Map.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-spellbooks#qWhatHappensWhenYouUseRecriminationsOnASpellbookThatContainsAMoonbeast","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I am playing Opener of the Way and use Recriminations to swap out Dragon Ascending or Dragon Descending after I have flipped them face-down, do they flip face-up again? Could I take those Spellbooks again (using Recriminations) and re-use them?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Spellbooks","text":"A. While you could take them back onto your Faction Card, you cannot flip them. The Spellbook states “flip it face down to indicate that it cannot be used again.” This is categorical. It also works this way with Crawling Chaos’ Thousand Forms, which won’t flip over until the following Gather Power Phase.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-spellbooks#qIfIAmPlayingOpenerOfTheWayAndUseRecriminationsToSwapOutDragonAscendingOrDragonDescendingAfterIHaveFlippedThemFaceDownDoTheyFlipFaceUpAgainCouldITakeThoseSpellbooksAgainUsingRecriminationsAndReUseThem","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Demand Sacrifice interact with the Leng Spiders’ Bloodthirst?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. Any Pains converted into Kills become single Pains. I recommend against using Bloodthirst!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qHowDoesDemandSacrificeInteractWithTheLengSpidersBloodthirst","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Bubastis’ Zagazig Spellbook interact with the Leng Spiders’ Bloodthirst?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. First, Zagazig swaps all rolled Kills and Pains. Then apply Bloodthirst to the resultant Pains.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qHowDoesBubastisZagazigSpellbookInteractWithTheLengSpidersBloodthirst","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Black Goat Summon a Neutral Monster at the same time as her Faction Monsters?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. Yes. She may Summon any number of Monsters at once, as long as they are hers to Summon.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qCanBlackGoatSummonANeutralMonsterAtTheSameTimeAsHerFactionMonsters","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Yellow Sign spawn Neutral Monsters as the result of a Desecration Attempt?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. Yes, so long as they cost 2 or fewer Power.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qCanYellowSignSpawnNeutralMonstersAsTheResultOfADesecrationAttempt","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Mind Control (the Elder Thing’s ability) work?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. In an Elder Thing’s Area, Cthulhu can’t Devour. He can still use Submerge and Y’Ha Nthlei, as those are Spellbooks, not Great Old One special abilities. This ability also works on Independent Great Old Ones (but only their special abilities, and not their Spellbooks). Nyarlathotep can’t use Harbinger, Azathoth can be Killed with a single Kill result, and so on. Shub-Niggurath can’t Avatar out of an Area containing an Elder Thing, but she could use Avatar to enter an Area containing an Elder Thing because she is not in that Area at the moment she uses her Avatar ability. (And the player controlling Bokrug could lose his Loyalty Card!)
In some cases, Mind Control can cancel the abilities of Great Old Ones. For example—if Tsathoggua is in an Elder Thing’s Area, then he can’t use Lethargy. If Ithaqua is in an Elder Thing’s Area, then Ferox is not in effect for any of his Cultists (of course, if an Elder Thing is merely in the same Area as one of Windwalker’s Cultists, but NOT in Ithaqua’s Area, Ferox is still in effect). Likewise, Abhoth could put a Filth Token in an Elder Thing’s Area, so long as Abhoth himself does not share an Area with an Elder Thing. Some Spellbooks might be affected, even though they are not directly negated by Elder Things. For example: The King in Yellow can’t Desecrate, which means that his Third Eye Spellbook can’t be used, either (a similar effect happens to Cthugha and Ghatanothoa when they have their respective Firestorm and Execration of Mu Spellbooks).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qHowDoesMindControlTheElderThingsAbilityWork","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Is there any way to get rid of the Servitor of the Outer Gods Loyalty Card once it has been given to you?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. No","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qIsThereAnyWayToGetRidOfTheServitorOfTheOuterGodsLoyaltyCardOnceItHasBeenGivenToYou","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I have been given Servitor of the Outer Gods, can I still gain non-Servitor Monsters by means other than Summoning?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. Yes. For example, Windwalker can use Cannibalism to place Wendigos, Opener of the Way can promote Units via Million Favored Ones, and Yellow Sign can place via Desecration attempts. The Servitor of the Outer Gods’ ability only affects normal Summons.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qIfIHaveBeenGivenServitorOfTheOuterGodsCanIStillGainNonServitorMonstersByMeansOtherThanSummoning","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Can I use Black Goat’s Fertility Cult ability tosimultaneously Summon all the remaining Servitorsin my Pool, as well as other Monsters?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. Yes, you can do this as long as no Servitors remain inyour Pool at the end of this Action.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#canIUseBlackGoatsFertilityCultAbilityTosimultaneouslySummonAllTheRemainingServitorsinMyPoolAsWellAsOtherMonsters","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If the presence of Servitors of the Outer Gods reduces my Combat total to less than zero, what happens?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. Just leave it at zero. That’s bad enough.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qIfThePresenceOfServitorsOfTheOuterGodsReducesMyCombatTotalToLessThanZeroWhatHappens","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What if I have both Star Vampires and Servitors of  the Outer Gods in the same Area, reducing my overall Combat dice to less than what the Star Vampires would normally roll, or even 0. How do I roll my Star Vampire dice “separately”?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. Just go ahead and roll your Star Vampires’ total Combat dice. In this case, you will actually get to roll Combat dice, even though your total is technically zero. However, if your total dice are technically zero, you cannot Declare Battle. Weird, I know, but if Servitors are in play, you’re already dealing with multiple realities and alternate dimensions. And yes, in this case, the Combat results of the Star Vampires still DO apply in the Battle, as usual.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qWhatIfIHaveBothStarVampiresAndServitorsOfTheOuterGodsInTheSameAreaReducingMyOverallCombatDiceToLessThanWhatTheStarVampiresWouldNormallyRollOrEven0HowDoIRollMyStarVampireDiceSeparately","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When a Star Vampire rolls a Kill or a Pain, in addition to the Doom or Power that is drained from the target, is the Kill or Pain inﬂicted on the Enemy?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. Yes, you always add the Star Vampire’s Combat results to the Battle (even if, as in the  question above, you technically have zero Combat dice). However, if the Enemy has no Power (or no Doom), then the Star Vampire’s drain does nothing.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qWhenAStarVampireRollsAKillOrAPainInAdditionToTheDoomOrPowerThatIsDrainedFromTheTargetIsTheKillOrPainInﬂictedOnTheEnemy","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What if my Star Vampires roll more Kill and/or Pain results than there are Enemy Units in the Battle?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. You still get to take the Doom and/or Power from your Enemy, even if some of the Battle results are not applied to Enemy Units (unless, of course, your Enemy doesn’t have enough Doom or Power to take). This also means, for example, that if Rhan Tegoth uses his Eternal ability when fighting your Star Vampires, you still get to take the Doom or Power if a Kill or Pain was initially assigned to Rhan Tegoth! Likewise, if your Star Vampire rolls a Kill against Nyarlathotep when he is protected by Emissary of the Outer Gods, you get 1 Doom but the Kill is reduced to a Pain (as per Emissary).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qWhatIfMyStarVampiresRollMoreKillAndOrPainResultsThanThereAreEnemyUnitsInTheBattle","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Yellow Sign Recruits a Dimensional Shambler (or Moonbeast) while attempting a Desecration, where does the Shambler appear?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. Sadly, in the Desecrated Area, as described in the ability. This also applies to Moonbeasts.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qIfYellowSignRecruitsADimensionalShamblerOrMoonbeastWhileAttemptingADesecrationWhereDoesTheShamblerAppear","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If a Moonbeast is placed on Great Cthulhu’s Submerge Spellbook when Cthulhu is currently oﬀ the map, does the Great Cthulhu player have to remove the Moonbeast before those units can return?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. A Spellbook action or effect that is partly complete remains that way and can be completed despite a Moonbeast’s cancellation. A new action or effect would be prevented. So for example, if Cthulhu has Submerged before the Moonbeast’s arrival, he can emerge. Similarly, if Sleeper has a Cursed Slumber Gate, it can remain where it is or return, but a new Gate can’t be Cursed.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qIfAMoonbeastIsPlacedOnGreatCthulhusSubmergeSpellbookWhenCthulhuIsCurrentlyOﬀTheMapDoesTheGreatCthulhuPlayerHaveToRemoveTheMoonbeastBeforeThoseUnitsCanReturn","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If a Moonbeast is placed on Black Goat’s Red Sign","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A. No. However, the Dark Young no longer provides Power during the Gather Power phase, and if it leaves the Gate cannot occupy a new one.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qIfAMoonbeastIsPlacedOnBlackGoatsRedSign","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: What does Elder Things’ Mind Control do against Baphomet?","type":"FAQ","product":"Neutral Monsters","text":"A: It disables Sacrament of Flesh. Hard to pull off, but utterly devastating to The Invasion if it happens. Unquenchable Thirst is unaffected as it cannot be disabled or deactivated.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/neutral-monsters#qWhatDoesElderThingsMindControlDoAgainstBaphomet","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does the Tcho-Tcho’s Soulless interact with the Yithian’s Possession ability?","type":"FAQ","product":"Terrors","text":"A. Soulless makes the base reward 0 Power, rather than 1. The Yithian’sPossession adds to whatever the base reward is, whether 1 or 0. Thus, aYithian who Captured a Soulless Tcho-Tcho still provides at least 1Power.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/terrors#qHowDoesTheTchoTchosSoullessInteractWithTheYithiansPossessionAbility","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If my Great Old One shares an enemy Cacodemon’sArea, can I pain other non-Great Old One Units intothat Area?","type":"FAQ","product":"Terrors","text":"A.No.They are not accompanied by a Great Old One.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/terrors#qIfMyGreatOldOneSharesAnEnemyCacodemonsAreaCanIPainOtherNonGreatOldOneUnitsIntothatArea","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If the Shadow Pharaoh is on the Moon, what happens to Bubastis’ control of the Moon Gate?","type":"FAQ","product":"Terrors","text":"A. Nothing. Like Yog-Sothoth, Bubastis’ Moon Gate is inherent and always present.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/terrors#qIfTheShadowPharaohIsOnTheMoonWhatHappensToBubastisControlOfTheMoonGate","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: Does the Shadow Pharaoh have any effect on Lord’s Shadows?","type":"FAQ","product":"Terrors","text":"A: No, they (like Yog) are Controlled Gates without having a Controlling Unit. However, The Invasion controlling the Shadow Pharaoh seems hilariously over-powered. Remember that with The Invasion it is virtually impossible for them to be First Player early in the game, so someone else should acquire Shadow Pharaoh before The Invasion can.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/terrors#qDoesTheShadowPharaohHaveAnyEffectOnLordsShadows","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can you combine placing Abhoth’s Filth with Black Goat’s FertilityCult? Or Sleeper’s Death from Below?Or Yellow Sign’s Desecration?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. YES to all!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qCanYouCombinePlacingAbhothsFilthWithBlackGoatsFertilityCultOrSleepersDeathFromBelowOrYellowSignsDesecration","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When I Control Azathoth, can I modify the Nuclear Chaos die roll to be 0 or 7?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Yes!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qWhenIControlAzathothCanIModifyTheNuclearChaosDieRollToBe0Or7","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Azathoth absorb more than one Kill result in a single Battle?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. No.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qCanAzathothAbsorbMoreThanOneKillResultInASingleBattle","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How much Power can Nyarlathotep get when he Pains or Kills Azathoth in Battle (under Harbinger)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Zero. Technically, Azathoth costs 0 Power to Awaken. The one die plus 2 Power you pay to Awaken him is a loss, not a cost. Nyarlathotep can get at most 2 Elder Signs when fighting Azathoth.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qHowMuchPowerCanNyarlathotepGetWhenHePainsOrKillsAzathothInBattleUnderHarbinger","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What happens when Azathoth is surrounded by Enemy Units he just Battled, and he receives a Pain?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Treat it as if he received a Kill and roll a die.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qWhatHappensWhenAzathothIsSurroundedByEnemyUnitsHeJustBattledAndHeReceivesAPain","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What happens when Azathoth is chosen to receive a Kill as a result of Dread Curse of Azathoth (since no Battle abilities apply)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Azathoth’s special ability is Ongoing and not a Battle ability, so just reduce his Combat by a d6. (Yog-Sothoth can’t use Azathoth’s own curse against him, you cadaverous fool! But because Azathoth is the Blind Idiot God, he can still harm himself somewhat).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qWhatHappensWhenAzathothIsChosenToReceiveAKillAsAResultOfDreadCurseOfAzathothSinceNoBattleAbilitiesApply","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Is Azathoth’s spellbook requirement; “...all players must have at least one Great Old One in play...”, achievable after The Ancients have all 4 Cathedrals in play?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. The Ancients are ignored for the purpose of Azathoth’s spellbook requirement.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qIsAzathothsSpellbookRequirementAllPlayersMustHaveAtLeastOneGreatOldOneInPlayAchievableAfterTheAncientsHaveAll4CathedralsInPlay","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Is the Bloated Woman’s Spellbook a constant eﬀect, or can you chooseto ignore it to gain Power as normal should you so choose?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. The Spellbook is not intended to be optional, so you may not choose to ignore it.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qIsTheBloatedWomansSpellbookAConstantEﬀectOrCanYouChoosetoIgnoreItToGainPowerAsNormalShouldYouSoChoose","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Is a Unit held on The Bloated Woman’s Loyalty Card available for Summon-like abilities such as Death From Below?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. No, Units on her Card are not considered in a player’s Pool. Theymust first be Summoned directly from The Bloated Woman’s Card.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qIsAUnitHeldOnTheBloatedWomansLoyaltyCardAvailableForSummonLikeAbilitiesSuchAsDeathFromBelow","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I have a Controlled Gate and only Units with 0 Combat, can I declare Battle due to Miri Nigri?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Yes! Although Miri Nigri does not technically add 3 Combat to aparticular Unit (as with Absorb), the fact that you will roll Combatdice means that you can initiate Battle even if all you have is a singleCultist (on that Gate) in the Area.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qIfIHaveAControlledGateAndOnlyUnitsWith0CombatCanIDeclareBattleDueToMiriNigri","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Chaugnar Faugn’s Miri Nigri ability gives Gates 3 Combat dice. Does this apply to Yog-Sothoth?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Yes! For example, if there are 4 Enemy Great Old Ones on the Map andan Opener-Controlled Chaugnar Faugn, then Yog-Sothoth’s Combat would be11 (8 + 3). However, if Opener also Controlled a normal Gate in the sameArea as Yog-Sothoth, you would still only add 3 to your Combat in thatArea, not 6. The ability reads “in an Area,” which means that you onlyget the Combat bonus once per Area, rather than once per Gate.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qChaugnarFaugnsMiriNigriAbilityGivesGates3CombatDiceDoesThisApplyToYogSothoth","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: How does Curse of Chaugnar Faugn work with Infernolatreia?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A: They hand you a number of Elder Signs equal to however many Lord’s Shadows you have, and you are able to choose amongst those. Assuming that you are not friends, you probably will have to deplete them of low-value Elder Signs prior to getting much use out of it.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qHowDoesCurseOfChaugnarFaugnWorkWithInfernolatreia","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: How does Curse of Chaugnar Faugn work with Blood Offering?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A: They give you the Elder Signs to reveal, you reveal them and make offers or a deal accordingly, and then return the rest to the “face up” Pool.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qHowDoesCurseOfChaugnarFaugnWorkWithBloodOffering","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Cthugha rolls a Kill on Rhan Tegoth, but the latter uses Eternalto cancel it, does Cthugha still have a chance to spare Rhan Tegoth,too?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. No, Eternal takes precedence—if Windwalker chooses to remove the Kill or Pain from Rhan Tegoth, Cthugha cannot spare him.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qIfCthughaRollsAKillOnRhanTegothButTheLatterUsesEternaltoCancelItDoesCthughaStillHaveAChanceToSpareRhanTegothToo","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does Cthugha copy the combat of Elder Gods?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Cthugha rolls no dice when facing an Elder God, and gets no further benefit vs. Elder Gods.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qDoesCthughaCopyTheCombatOfElderGods","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When using Non-Euclidean to assign combat results to a third party,can they use non-Battle Spellbooks and abilities such as Yellow Sign’sPassion?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Affected third party Factions cannot use Battle Spellbooks orabilities. They can still benefit from non-Battle Spellbooks andabilities.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qWhenUsingNonEuclideanToAssignCombatResultsToAThirdPartyCanTheyUseNonBattleSpellbooksAndAbilitiesSuchAsYellowSignsPassion","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Units Pained by Non-Euclidean enter Areas with Units from Dire Cthulhu’s controlling Faction?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Affected third party Factions cannot use Battle Spellbooks orabilities. They can still benefit from non-Battle Spellbooks andabilities.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qCanUnitsPainedByNonEuclideanEnterAreasWithUnitsFromDireCthulhusControllingFaction","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can the Non-Euclidean Spellbook target Units that have been removedfrom Battle? (i.e. Flying Polyp using the Invisibility Spellbook)","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. No.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qCanTheNonEuclideanSpellbookTargetUnitsThatHaveBeenRemovedfromBattleIEFlyingPolypUsingTheInvisibilitySpellbook","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can a Brood be Moved via Cursed Slumber, since it’s not really a “movement-like” ability?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. No, you may not use Cursed Slumber on a Brood, as you can go toanother Area on the Map! Brood are already in a terrible slumber…","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qCanABroodBeMovedViaCursedSlumberSinceItsNotReallyAMovementLikeAbility","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does the Tcho-Tcho’s Soulless interact with Gla’aki’s Green Decay?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Soulless makes the base reward 0 Power, rather than 1. Gla’aki’sGreen Decay modifies that reward to be an Elder Sign (meaning that itoverrides Soulless by changing its reward from Power to an Elder Sign).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qHowDoesTheTchoTchosSoullessInteractWithGlaakisGreenDecay","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Nodens copies The Ancients’ Extinction Spellbook, is He removed from the game upon being killed or eliminated?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. No.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qIfNodensCopiesTheAncientsExtinctionSpellbookIsHeRemovedFromTheGameUponBeingKilledOrEliminated","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When Awakening Nyogtha, how many Elder Signs does Great Cthulhu receive? If a Nyogtha unit is killed and re-awakened, does Great Cthulhu receive another Elder Sign?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Cthulhu gains 1 Elder Sign upon Awakening Nyogtha. If only 1 of 2Nyogtha units is Awakened, Great Cthulhu does not receive an Elder Sign.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qWhenAwakeningNyogthaHowManyElderSignsDoesGreatCthulhuReceiveIfANyogthaUnitIsKilledAndReAwakenedDoesGreatCthulhuReceiveAnotherElderSign","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How do two “simultaneous” Battles occur? Is one Battle fully resolvedbefore the other? Can your Units from the ﬁrst Battle be Pained to thesecond?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. The Battles must be in different Areas. One is fully resolved beforethe other, and Units from the first Battle who are Pained to the secondcan participate in the second.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qHowDoTwoSimultaneousBattlesOccurIsOneBattleFullyResolvedbeforeTheOtherCanYourUnitsFromTheFIrstBattleBePainedToThesecond","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If both Nyogtha Units are in the same Area, do they each add 4 Combat dice when the owner declares Battle?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qIfBothNyogthaUnitsAreInTheSameAreaDoTheyEachAdd4CombatDiceWhenTheOwnerDeclaresBattle","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can two Nyogtha Units in the same Area cause two Battles to happen in that Area?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. No.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qCanTwoNyogthaUnitsInTheSameAreaCauseTwoBattlesToHappenInThatArea","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If only one of the two Nyogtha Units is Killed or Eliminated inBattle, does this trigger any eﬀects related to the Elimination of aGreat Old One?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. No, both Nyogtha Units must be Killed / Eliminated.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qIfOnlyOneOfTheTwoNyogthaUnitsIsKilledOrEliminatedInBattleDoesThisTriggerAnyEﬀectsRelatedToTheEliminationOfAGreatOldOne","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Nyarlathotep get 4 Elder Signs for hitting both Nyogtha ﬁgures inthe same Area or is he awarded 2 since it is the same Great Old One?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. He only gets 2, whether he Kills or Pains one or both Nyogtha figures.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qCanNyarlathotepGet4ElderSignsForHittingBothNyogthaFIguresIntheSameAreaOrIsHeAwarded2SinceItIsTheSameGreatOldOne","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If a Nyogtha Unit is Killed in Battle, but the other Unit survives ina diﬀerent Area, does this count towards Nyogtha’s Spellbookrequirement?","type":"FAQ","product":"Independent Great Old Ones","text":"A. No. All Nyogtha Units in the Areas where the Battle(s) happened must survive.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/independent-great-old-ones#qIfANyogthaUnitIsKilledInBattleButTheOtherUnitSurvivesInaDiﬀerentAreaDoesThisCountTowardsNyogthasSpellbookrequirement","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If I Awaken The King in Yellow (as an Independent Great Old One) via Lavinia Whateley, do I get a refund of 1 Power?","type":"FAQ","product":"Unique High Priests","text":"A. Yes","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/unique-high-priests#qIfIAwakenTheKingInYellowAsAnIndependentGreatOldOneViaLaviniaWhateleyDoIGetARefundOf1Power","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When I have Lavinia Whateley, how do I calculate Awakening Cthugha?","type":"FAQ","product":"Unique High Priests","text":"A. Lavinia Whateley reduces the cost to Awaken Cthugha himself, notwhichever Great Old One Cthugha will replace as part of Awakening him.For example, if you have Hastur and want to Awaken Cthugha, the costwould be calculated by starting with 6, then subtracting 3 (per Lavinia), and then again subtracting 10 (the nominal cost to Awaken Hastur). The result would be negative 7. Then, per Cthugha’s Awakening requirements, you would gain Power equal to the result if itis negative, so you would GAIN 7 Power by Awakening Cthugha using bothHastur and Lavinia Whateley.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/unique-high-priests#qWhenIHaveLaviniaWhateleyHowDoICalculateAwakeningCthugha","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. When I use Asenath Waite’s The Thing From Beyond, where does my replacement Unit come from?","type":"FAQ","product":"Unique High Priests","text":"A. Your Pool.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/unique-high-priests#qWhenIUseAsenathWaitesTheThingFromBeyondWhereDoesMyReplacementUnitComeFrom","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Do I win as Opener of the Way if I Control 4 Gates at Citadels,including Yog-Sothoth, but only in 3 of the Citadel Areas (e.g., IControl Gates in Citadel Areas numbered with 1, 2, & 3, andYog-Sothoth itself is also in Citadel three, but I do NOT control a Gatein the Area of Citadel four)?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No. You must Control Gates in all four Areas, not simply Control fourGates among the Citadel Areas, you cheater. In this situation, MovingYog-Sothoth to Citadel 4 would give you the win.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qDoIWinAsOpenerOfTheWayIfIControl4GatesAtCitadelsIncludingYogSothothButOnlyIn3OfTheCitadelAreasEGIControlGatesInCitadelAreasNumberedWith123AndYogSothothItselfIsAlsoInCitadelThreeButIDoNotControlAGateinTheAreaOfCitadelFour","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What happens if I ﬁght three Zoogs and roll two Kills and three Pains? How many of my Units are affected by the reﬂected Pains?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. First, remove the Killed Zoogs. Only one remains, so it is Pained(and removed), and one of your Units is likewise Pained. Remember, Killsalways take effect before Pains.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qWhatHappensIfIFIghtThreeZoogsAndRollTwoKillsAndThreePainsHowManyOfMyUnitsAreAffectedByTheReﬂectedPains","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Black Goat’s Necrophagy interact with the Zoogs?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. If two Ghouls teleport via Necrophagy to a Battle in which Zoogs haveparticipated, two of the original attacker’s Units are Pained asnormal, and two Zoogs are likewise Pained (and removed). Both Ghouls arealso Pained by the Zoogs (the original Attacker receives Pains due toNecrophagy, but not additional Pains as a result of the Zoogs beingPained by Necrophagy—those Pains are reflected back on the Ghoulsthemselves).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qHowDoesBlackGoatsNecrophagyInteractWithTheZoogs","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Cthulhu count Zoogs which are Eliminated by Pain results as Kills for the purpose of his Spellbook requirements?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes. Even though Avatar specifically works on Faction Monsters, Zoogsare all identical so it doesn’t matter which one in the given Area ischosen to swap places with Shub-Niggurath. If the Zoog is sent viaAvatar to an Area that is NOT a Citadel, then the Zoog is Eliminatedfrom the Map.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanCthulhuCountZoogsWhichAreEliminatedByPainResultsAsKillsForThePurposeOfHisSpellbookRequirements","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Opener of the Way’s Dread Curse of Azathoth be used to attack the Bhole or Zoogs?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanOpenerOfTheWaysDreadCurseOfAzathothBeUsedToAttackTheBholeOrZoogs","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Shub-Niggurath use her Avatar ability to switch places with a Zoog?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes. Even though Avatar specifically works on Faction Monsters, Zoogsare all identical so it doesn’t matter which one in the given Area ischosen to swap places with Shub-Niggurath. If the Zoog is sent viaAvatar to an Area that is NOT a Citadel, then the Zoog is Eliminatedfrom the Map.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanShubNiggurathUseHerAvatarAbilityToSwitchPlacesWithAZoog","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Zoogs be captured via Sleeper’s Capture Monster?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Of course, and it will remain captured until it is sacrificed in the Gather Power Phase.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanZoogsBeCapturedViaSleepersCaptureMonster","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does the Shantaks’ Horror Steed ability allow it to Move freely between the two maps?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qDoesTheShantaksHorrorSteedAbilityAllowItToMoveFreelyBetweenTheTwoMaps","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If the Custodian Moves my Units to The Oubliette, and an Abandoned Gate is there, can I immediately occupy it?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Only when it is your turn to take an Action.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qIfTheCustodianMovesMyUnitsToTheOublietteAndAnAbandonedGateIsThereCanIImmediatelyOccupyIt","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. To Battle the player who currently has the Barrier of Naach Tith Tome, must I release a Captured Cultist from that Faction?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No. You can release a Captured Cultist from any Faction to bypass the Barrier.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qToBattleThePlayerWhoCurrentlyHasTheBarrierOfNaachTithTomeMustIReleaseACapturedCultistFromThatFaction","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. What if I want to Battle the owner of Barrier of Naach Tith, and Idon’t have a Captured Cultist, a Silence Token, nor an Elder Sign?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes, but you must have had at least one Power to take the Action.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qWhatIfIWantToBattleTheOwnerOfBarrierOfNaachTithAndIdontHaveACapturedCultistASilenceTokenNorAnElderSign","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If the Librarian or Custodian are Activated in the same Area over several Actions in a row, do they keep adding +1 more to their Agony die roll, accumulating over time?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No. They just get a maximum of +1 to their roll.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qIfTheLibrarianOrCustodianAreActivatedInTheSameAreaOverSeveralActionsInARowDoTheyKeepAdding1MoreToTheirAgonyDieRollAccumulatingOverTime","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does Windwalker’s Ice Age defend against the Librarian or the Custodian?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No, because the action to trigger the Librarian or Custodian does not technically take place in the Librarian’s or Custodian’s Area.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qDoesWindwalkersIceAgeDefendAgainstTheLibrarianOrTheCustodian","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. I think the Map layout for Primeval Earth is interesting, and I wouldlike to try playing it in a normal game, without the Glaciers. Wouldthis work?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. It’s your game. Give it a try! Then try Glaciers on Yuggoth!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qIThinkTheMapLayoutForPrimevalEarthIsInterestingAndIWouldlikeToTryPlayingItInANormalGameWithoutTheGlaciersWouldthisWork","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If Opener of the Way uses Beyond One to Move a Gate from aGlacier-infested Area to a clear Area, does the Glacier travel with theGate?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No. The Glacier is removed from the Gate in this case. If a Gate is Moved to where there is a Glacier, the Glacier immediately pops on topof it.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qIfOpenerOfTheWayUsesBeyondOneToMoveAGateFromAGlacierInfestedAreaToAClearAreaDoesTheGlacierTravelWithTheGate","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How do the Glaciers work with Cursed Slumber?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Since you can only use Cursed Slumber with a Controlled Gate, thenyou may not use it in an Area already containing a Glacier. However, ifyou place a Cursed Slumbering Gate back on the Map onto an Area with a Glacier, then the Cultist must immediately step off the Gate.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qHowDoTheGlaciersWorkWithCursedSlumber","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Opener’s They Break Through Spellbook be used to Summon Monsters at a Gate covered by a Glacier?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes. They Break Through permits you to Summon at Abandoned Gates.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanOpenersTheyBreakThroughSpellbookBeUsedToSummonMonstersAtAGateCoveredByAGlacier","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. In the ﬁrst Doom Phase, do I add a Glacier to the Start Areas of Factions not in this game?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qInTheFIrstDoomPhaseDoIAddAGlacierToTheStartAreasOfFactionsNotInThisGame","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Theoretically, the Daemon Sultan faction could Pass, and thus not geta Start Area in the ﬁrst turn. If he does, does he get an automaticGlacier in his Start on the second turn?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qTheoreticallyTheDaemonSultanFactionCouldPassAndThusNotGetaStartAreaInTheFIrstTurnIfHeDoesDoesHeGetAnAutomaticGlacierInHisStartOnTheSecondTurn","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does Crawling Chaos avoid losing a Unit with his Flight ability when “skipping” over Eradicated Areas?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No. He must lose a Unit to trace over such Areas, though skippingover an Eradicated Area doesn’t count as Moving over an Area for Flight, so he could Move over three Areas if one of them were Eradicated.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qDoesCrawlingChaosAvoidLosingAUnitWithHisFlightAbilityWhenSkippingOverEradicatedAreas","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does Yellow Sign get his Passion Power when his cultists are Eradicated?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qDoesYellowSignGetHisPassionPowerWhenHisCultistsAreEradicated","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does Yog-Sothoth give Opener two Elder Signs if he is Eradicated?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes, because he is not only a faction Great Old One but also a Gate. You’d also get 1 Power, since he is a Unit.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qDoesYogSothothGiveOpenerTwoElderSignsIfHeIsEradicated","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Windwalker use Cosmic Power to pay 8 Power and summon Ithaqua “on top of” Yog-Sothoth, thus killing the latter?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Only if Yog-Sothoth is the only Gate in the Area. Otherwise, Windwalker must destroy the normal Gate.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanWindwalkerUseCosmicPowerToPay8PowerAndSummonIthaquaOnTopOfYogSothothThusKillingTheLatter","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can a Worm of Groth be placed on the Bubastis Moon tile?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No, it is not considered adjacent to any Area except for Bubastis, and cats don't bring Worms home.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanAWormOfGrothBePlacedOnTheBubastisMoonTile","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does the Bubastis faction fulﬁll the Spellbook requirement: “...a Cat is in every other faction’s Start Area...” when starting Areas aredestroyed?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Bubastis is allowed to use the \"Pay 6 Power\" rule but not the \"Pay2 Power\" rule even though the Moon can't have a Worm. Cats are likethat.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qHowDoesTheBubastisFactionFulﬁllTheSpellbookRequirementACatIsInEveryOtherFactionsStartAreaWhenStartingAreasAredestroyed","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does a Retreat across a destroyed Area on the Shaggai Map also cost an Elimination to the Retreating Units?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. You cannot Retreat across an Eradicated Area. If you cannot Retreatdue to this, you lose a Unit as with any other blocked Pain result.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qDoesARetreatAcrossADestroyedAreaOnTheShaggaiMapAlsoCostAnEliminationToTheRetreatingUnits","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Bubastis ignore Eradicated Areas for the “Be in all Start Areas” Spellbook requirement?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No. But She can use the “Pay 6 Power” rule.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanBubastisIgnoreEradicatedAreasForTheBeInAllStartAreasSpellbookRequirement","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can the Daemon Sultan’s Chaos Gate move through a destroyed area with Animate Matter?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes, but the Controlling Unit is Eliminated.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanTheDaemonSultansChaosGateMoveThroughADestroyedAreaWithAnimateMatter","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does the Leng Tribe’s Dark Rituals work when an enemy Faction’s Start Area has been destroyed?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. The Dark Rituals Spellbook works normally - but since no High Priestmay move to an Eradicated area, factions whose Start Areas are gone areimmune.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qHowDoesTheLengTribesDarkRitualsWorkWhenAnEnemyFactionsStartAreaHasBeenDestroyed","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q: How does Shaggai’s destroyed Areas work with Lord’s Shadows / Portents?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A: If you have any amount of Portents in a destroyed Area, you earn 1 Elder Sign total (not per Portent).
\nA: If you have a Lord’s Shadow in a destroyed Area, you would earn 2 Elder Signs (Provided that you control it) (keep in mind that this would lower the effect of Infernolatreia PRIOR to Infernolatreia triggering).
\nA: If you had a Fiend-Controlled Gate in an Area with a Lord’s Shadow, you’d still just earn 2 Elder Signs, and, like above, Infernolatreia would be weakened prior to triggering. The effects of the Lord’s Shadow override the effects of the Map. This means you do not get an additional Elder Sign for the normal Gate. But don’t worry, we know that you didn’t build that Gate anyway; it likely belonged to someone else.
\nA: If another player had a Controlled Gate in an Area with a Lord’s Shadow, they would receive 1 Elder Sign per usual (as this effect counts Areas, not number of Gates in that Area. However, The Invasion (not controlling that Lord’s Shadow) would receive nothing!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qHowDoesShaggaisDestroyedAreasWorkWithLordsShadowsPortents","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Cthulhu get his Kill Spellbook requirements from scoring a Kill on the Watcher?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes! (But not for Devour, since that doesn’t affect the Watcher).","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanCthulhuGetHisKillSpellbookRequirementsFromScoringAKillOnTheWatcher","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. I have two Units in an Area, one of which is a Brain Cylinder. InBattle, the enemy rolls one Kill and one Pain. What are my options?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Kills are always assigned first. If you assign the Kill to the Cylinder, it dies and the other Unit is Pained. If you assign the Kill to the other Unit, then the Pain is ignored.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qIHaveTwoUnitsInAnAreaOneOfWhichIsABrainCylinderInBattleTheEnemyRollsOneKillAndOnePainWhatAreMyOptions","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Windwalker’s Howl Retreat a Brain Cylinder?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No. Brain Cylinders turn off their sensors, so they don’t hear the Howl.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanWindwalkersHowlRetreatABrainCylinder","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does Black Goat’s Frenzy aﬀect Brain Cylinders?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes. This represents them casting spells, planning strategy, or cheering others on.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qDoesBlackGoatsFrenzyAﬀectBrainCylinders","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Yellow Sign’s Passion Spellbook apply to Brain Cylinders?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. When a Brain Cylinder is either directly Captured or Converted to an Enemy Brain Cylinder, Yellow Sign gains 1 Power if Passion is in play (his Cultist has been lost!). Of course, Yellow Sign does not gain 1 Power when removing his own Acolyte in order to replace it with a Brain Cylinder.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qHowDoesYellowSignsPassionSpellbookApplyToBrainCylinders","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How does Ghatanothoa’s Mummify ability aﬀect Brain Cylinders?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Brain Cylinders are immune to Mummify. They are only brains, and according to Lovecraft, they are not affected by the mummification process. Also, Mummify specifies “Acolyte Cultist,” you n00b.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qHowDoesGhatanothoasMummifyAbilityAﬀectBrainCylinders","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. If a Battle takes place on the Slime Sea Overlook and the Gate’s Controller is Pained or Killed, can his enemy Retreat into an adjacentArea containing only Slimes?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes, because the Slimes are now uncontrolled!","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qIfABattleTakesPlaceOnTheSlimeSeaOverlookAndTheGatesControllerIsPainedOrKilledCanHisEnemyRetreatIntoAnAdjacentAreaContainingOnlySlimes","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. How is the Watcher affected by Elder Things?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. The Elder Things’ Mind Control ability has no effect on the Watcher.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qHowIsTheWatcherAffectedByElderThings","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Opener of the Way’s Dread Curse of Azathoth be used to attack the Watcher or uncontrolled Slimes?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanOpenerOfTheWaysDreadCurseOfAzathothBeUsedToAttackTheWatcherOrUncontrolledSlimes","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Shub-Niggurath use her Avatar ability to switch places with an uncontrolled Slime Mold?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes. Even though Avatar specifically works on Faction units, Slime Molds are identical, so it doesn’t matter which one in the given Area ischosen to swap places with Shub-Niggurath.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanShubNiggurathUseHerAvatarAbilityToSwitchPlacesWithAnUncontrolledSlimeMold","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Does the Watcher count as an enemy Great Old One for Windwalker’sHibernate ability? Does he prevent Opener of the Way from using Beyond One?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. Yes to both, but only when it is Awake. He is always considered an enemy Great Old One.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qDoesTheWatcherCountAsAnEnemyGreatOldOneForWindwalkersHibernateAbilityDoesHePreventOpenerOfTheWayFromUsingBeyondOne","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]},{"name":"Q. Can Sleeper use Death from Below or Yellow Sign use Desecration to place a Slime Mold?","type":"FAQ","product":"Additional Maps","text":"A. No, Slime Molds may only be placed via the Call Slime Mold Action.","img":"/rulebook/icon-faq-result.png","url":"/rulebook/additional-maps#qCanSleeperUseDeathFromBelowOrYellowSignUseDesecrationToPlaceASlimeMold","keywords":["rulebook","faq"]}]

    // Keep in Index only fitered
    function onlyFiltered(value) {
      return toFilter.some(e => value.keywords.includes(e));
    }

    // If no filter applied, all contents are shown
    if (toFilter.length > 0) {
      var filteredIndex = index.filter(onlyFiltered);
      index = filteredIndex;
    }

    matchList.classList.remove("d-none");
    clearSearchButton.classList.remove("d-none");
    const searchTextLowercased = searchText.toLowerCase();

    // Get matches to current text input
    const matches = index.map(entry => {
      let points = 0;
      if (entry.name.toLowerCase().startsWith(searchTextLowercased)) {
        points += 2;
      }
      if (entry.name.toLowerCase().includes(searchTextLowercased)) {
        points += 2;
      }
      if (entry.type.toLowerCase().includes(searchTextLowercased)) {
        points += 1;
      }
      if (entry.text) {
        if (entry.text.toLowerCase().includes(searchTextLowercased)) {
          points += 1;
        }
      }
      if (entry.product) {
        if (entry.product.toLowerCase().includes(searchTextLowercased)) {
          points += 1;
        }
      }
      return {
        ...entry,
        points
      };
    }).sort((a, b) => b.points - a.points);

    // Clear when input or matches are empty
    if (searchText.length === 0) {
      clearSearch();
    }
    outputHtml(matches.filter(matches => matches.points > 0));
  };

  // Show results in HTML
  var outputHtml = matches => {

    if (matches.length > 0) {
      if (matches.length > 30) {
        matches.length = 30;
      }

      matchList.innerHTML = "";

      matchList.append(...matches.map(function(match) {
        if (!(match.text)) {
          match.text = ""
        }

        const templateMatchSearchNav = document.getElementById('templateMatchSearchNav').content.cloneNode(true);

        templateMatchSearchNav.querySelector('a').href = match.url;
        templateMatchSearchNav.querySelector('.component-icon-slot').style = "background-image: url('/img/" + match.img;
        templateMatchSearchNav.querySelector('.result-name').textContent = match.name;
        templateMatchSearchNav.querySelector('.found-in').textContent = "In " + match.product;
        templateMatchSearchNav.querySelector('.result-type').textContent = match.type;

        if (match.type != "FAQ") {
          templateMatchSearchNav.getElementById('resultText').innerHTML = match.text;
        }

        return templateMatchSearchNav

      }));
    } else {
      matchList.innerHTML = "";
      const templateNoResult = document.getElementById('templateNoResult').content.cloneNode(true);
      templateNoResult.getElementById('resultText').innerHTML = "No results found";
      matchList.append(templateNoResult)
      // clearSearch();
    }
  };

body.script:
var loginButton = document.getElementById('buttonAccount');
var videoNoSleep = document.getElementById("video-nosleep");
var buttonSearch = document.getElementById('buttonSearch');
var dropdownSearch = document.getElementById('dropdownSearch');
var backButton = document.getElementById('backButton');

if (window.location.pathname === '/') {
  backButton.classList.add('d-none');
} else {
  backButton.classList.remove('d-none');
}

buttonSearch.addEventListener('click', function(){
  dropdownSearch.classList.toggle('search-dropdown-closed');
  buttonSearch.querySelector('i').classList.toggle('navbar-element-on')
});
